<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Thu, 17 Aug 95 12:30:44 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Papua New Guinea: Earthquake  DHA-01



                       PAPUA NEW GUINEA  - EARTHQUAKE
                          INFORMATION REPORT NO. 1
                               17 AUGUST 1995
 

  1.    ON 16 AUGUST AT  10:27 GMT OR 8:27 PM LOCAL TIME AN EARTHQUAKE WITH
A  MAGNITUDE OF 7.8 ON THE OPEN-ENDED RICHTER SCALE OCCURRED IN THE PACIFIC
OCEAN OFF THE COASTS OF BOUGAINVILLE,NEW BRITAIN AND NEW IRELAND.

  2.      THE EPICENTRE WAS DETERMINATED IN THE SOLOMON SEA ABOUT 270
  KM  SOUTHEAST OF THE PORT TOWN OF RABAUL (800 KM NORTHEAST OF  PORT
  MORESBY)  ON  THE ISLAND OF NEW BRITAIN AND 50 KM OF THE EAST COAST
  OF  BOUGANVILLE.  THE PRELIMARY HYPOCENTRE WAS AT A LATITUDE OF 5.7
  DEGREES SOUTH, LONGITUDE 154.1 DEGREES EAST AND A NORMAL DEPTH.

  3.      ONLY  MINOR  DAMAGE WAS REPORTED.FIVE LANDSLIDES CAUSED THE
  CUT  OFF  THE  RABAUL/KOKOPO ROAD AND ONE LANDSLIDE OCCURRED AT THE
  BLUE  LAGOON  ON  THE  ISLAND  OF  NEW  BRITAIN. PEOPLE IN THE CARE
  CENTRES  NEAR  THE KOKOPO ROAD WERE MOVED INLAND AS A PRECAUTIONARY
  MEASURE.  THE TOWN OF RABAUL WAS DEVASTATED LAST SEPTEMBER WHEN TWO
  VOLCANOS ERUPTED PROMPTING THE EVACUATION OF 30.000 PEOPLE.

  4.      THIS  IS  THE SECOND EARTHQUAKE IN TWO DAYS AND AFTERSHOCKS
  ARE  EXPECTED.  PREVIOUSLY  ON  14  AUGUST  AN  EARTHQUAKE  WITH  A
  MAGNITUDE  OF  6.2  ON THE OPEN-ENDED RICHTER SCALE WAS ONLY WEAKLY
  FELT.  THE  EPICENTRE WAS 100 KM SOUTHEAST OF RABAUL IN THE SOLOMON
  SEA.

  5.      A TSUNAMI WATCH AND WARNING HAS BEEN ISSUED FOR THE WESTERN
  PACIFIC  OCEAN  AND  A TSUNAMI WATCH ISSUED FOR THE WESTERN PACIFIC
  OCEAN SINCE ANY QUAKE AT SEA MEASURING 7 OR ABOVE ON THE OPEN-ENDED
  RICHTER SCALE CAN SET OFF TIDAL WAVES SEVERAL METERS HIGH AND CAUSE
  EXTENSIVE FLOODING IN COSTAL AREAS.

  6.     DHA/UNDP RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE IN PORT MORESBY HAS BEEN IN
  CONTACT  WITH  THE  OFFICE  OF  THE NATIONAL DISASTER AND EMERGENCY
  SERVICES.

  7.       NO   REQUEST  FOR  INTERNATIONAL  ASSISTANCE  RECEIVED  BY
  DHA-GENEVA.


  TELEPHONE NO: +4122-917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY TEL. NO.: +41-22-917.20.10
  DESK OFFICER:         G. MORTIER, DIRECT TEL. +41-22-917.13.94
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22-917.2856

  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22-917.00.23
  INTERNET EMAIL: DHAGVA AT UN.ORG

  FILE  DPR PNG

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +


distributed by
