Subject: Cuba: Hurricane  DHA-01


                              CUBA - HURRICANE
                    DHA - GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO.1
                               2 AUGUST  1995


  1.    IN  VIEW OF POSSIBLE NEGATIVE IMPACT BY HURRICANE ERIN THAT DID NOT
DIRECTLY  HIT  CUBA,  CIVIL  DEFENCE  SYSTEMS WERE  PUT ON ALERT THROUGHOUT
COUNTRY WITH EMPHASIS ON EASTERN PROVINCES.

  2.      THE  AUTHORITIES  EVACUATED  MORE  THAN  10,000 PEOPLE FROM
  LOW-LYING  AREAS IN PROVINCE OF GUANTANAMO (EASTERNMOST PROVINCE OF
  CUBA) AND LIVESTOCK WAS MOVE TO HIGH LEVEL PLACES.

  3.      NEGATIVE  CONSEQUENCES OF HURRICANE ERIN WERE INSIGNIFICANT
  AND HURRICANE ERIN IS NOW MOVING WEST-NORT-WEST.

