Date: Wed, 9 Aug 95 11:41:17 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Emergency Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Guatemala: Floods/Landslides  DHA-01


                     GUATEMALA -- FLOODS AND LANDSLIDES
                     DHA GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO. 1
                                9 AUGUST 1995


  1.    HEAVY  RAINS  CAUSED  FLOODS  AND  LANDSLIDES  ALL  OVER GUATEMALA,
AFFECTING  AN  ESTIMATED  7,100  PEOPLE,  ACCORDING TO INITIAL GOVERNMENTAL
REPORT.   MANY RIVERS, INCLUDING EL NARANJO, CHIBUJ, MARIA LINDA, COYOLATE,
MILAGRO, PEPOPTUM, AND SANTIAGO RIVERS, ARE SWELLING.

  2.        IN  DEPARTMENT  OF  SAN MARCOS IN SOUTHWESTERN GUATEMALA,
  3,000  PEOPLE  ARE  REPORTED  AFFECTED  IN  MUNICIPALITIES OF NUEVO
  PROGRESO,  MALACATAN,  EL QUETZAL, AND LA REFORMA.  TWO PEOPLE DEAD
  AND  SEVEN  MISSING.   IN  DEPARTMENTS  OF ESCUINTLA AND RETALHULEU
  ALONG  PACIFIC  COAST,  ABOUT 4,000 PEOPLE ARE REPORTED AFFECTED IN
  MUNICIPALITIES  OF  LA  GOMERA  AND  IZTAPA.  DAMAGE, INCLUDING ONE
  DEAD,  IS  ALSO  REPORTED  IN  GUATEMALA  CITY  AND  DEPARTMENTS OF
  CHIQUIMULA AND EL PROGRESO IN EASTERN GUATEMALA.

  3.      FLOODS  AND  LANDSLIDES  DAMAGED SEVERAL ROADS AND BRIDGES.
  280 PEOPLE ARE IN NEED OF SHELTER.

  4.      COMITE NACIONAL DE EMERGENCIA (CONE) AND LOCAL RESCUE TEAMS
  HAVE  BEEN  DEPLOYED  TO  MOST  AFFECTED  AREAS.  CONE REPORTS THAT
  NATIONAL  AUTHORITIES  ARE  CONSIDERING DECLARING NATIONAL STATE OF
  EMERGENCY,   IN   WHICH  CASE  FORMAL  REQUESTS  OR  APPEALS  COULD
  EVENTUALLY BE LAUNCHED.

  5.      ASSISTANCE  NEEDS  INCLUDE  PRIMARY  HEALTH-CARE MEDICINES,
  BASIC  FOODS,  CLOTHING,  HOUSEHOLD  TOOLS,  SHELTERING  EQUIPMENT,
  CONSTRUCTION  MATERIALS,  AND  DEPLOYMENT  OF  HEAVY  MACHINERY  TO
  REHABILITATE DAMAGED ROADS.

  6.     GOVT INSTITUTION IN CHARGE OF EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT IS COMITE
  NACIONAL   DE   EMERGENCIA   (TEL   502-2-321189   OR  326003,  FAX
  502-2-326716).

  7.     DHA, THROUGH UNDP/DHA RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE, IS MONITORING
  SITUATION.


  TELEPHONE NO.   +41-22/917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TEL NO. +41-22/917.20.10

  DESK OFFICER:   MS. K. GOTOH, DIRECT TEL. +41-22/917.12.58
  PRESS   TO   CONTACT:    MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22/917.28.56

  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH
  FAX:  +41-22/917.00.23
  ELECTRONIC MAIL:  INTERNET DHAGVA AT UN. ORG

  DPR 310 GUA

