Date: Wed, 6 Sep 95 12:14:54 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Philippines: Floods  DHA-01


                      PHILIPPINES - FLOODS
                     INFORMATION REPORT NO.1
                        5 SEPTEMBER 1995

SITUATION

1. UN RESIDENT COORDINATOR ISSUED CONSOLIDATED REPORT ON DAMAGE
CAUSED BY TORRENTIAL RAINS TO NORTHERN AND CENTRAL LUZON
INCLUDING METRO MANILA AREA, BROUGHT BY TYPHOON GENING
(INTERNATIONAL CODE NAME KENT).

 2. NUMBER OF PERSONS AFFECTED IN REGIONS I, III, IV, V AND
NATIONAL CAPITAL REGION (METRO MANILA) TOTALLED 178,803 OR 36,008
FAMILIES.  CASUALTIES TOTALLED 4.

3. IN PROVINCE OF ILOCOS NORTE, DAMAGE TO INFRASTRUCTURE AND
AGRICULTURE MOUNTS TO ABOUT USD 252,000 (P 6,407 MILLION).
PROVINCE OF BATANES WAS DEVASTATED, BUT CONFIRMED DETAILS ARE NOT
YET AVAILABLE DUE TO DESTRUCTION OF COMMUNICATION LINES.

4. LAHAR WARNING SIGNAL NO.1 REMAINS IN EFFECT OVER THE
MUNICIPALITIES OF PAMPANGA, ZAMBALES AND TARLAC.  11
MUNICIPALITIES IN PAMPANGA AND 1 IN BATAAN ARE STILL SUBMERGED IN
FLOOD WATERS.

5. TYPHOON HELMING (INTERNATIONAL CODE NAME NINA) CROSSED OVER
LUZON ON 4 SEPTEMBER, CAUSING HEAVY RAINS.  IT WAS THE SECOND
WEATHER DISTURBANCE TO HIT THE PHILIPPINES IN A WEEK.  CONFIRMED
ASSESSMENT OF DAMAGE IS NOT YET AVAILABLE.

NATIONAL RESPONSE

6. IN REGION I, CASH, RICE AND READY-TO-EAT FOOD WERE DISTRIBUTED
BY GOVERNMENT UNITS.  IN REGION III, 2,264 PERSONS OR 475
FAMILIES WERE RESCUED.  TWO HELICOPTERS WERE DISPATCHED TO
SUPPORT OPERATIONS.  LARGE NUMBER OF PEOPLE FLED ON THEIR OWN OR
WERE EVACUATED BY GOVERNMENT.  RELIEF OPERATIONS ARE CONTINUOUSLY
BEING CONDUCTED IN PAMPANGA.

7. AS YET, NO INTERNATIONAL APPEAL HAS BEEN ISSUED BY THE
GOVERNMENT.

