                           TOGO - TORRENTIAL RAINS
                            SITUATION REPORT NO.1
                                18 JULY 1995



  1.    DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE IN TOGO, REPORTED THAT TORRENTIAL
RAINS  CAUSED  FLASH  FLOODS  IN  THE CAPITAL, LOME, AFFECTING SERIOUSLY  A
GREAT NUMBER OF ITS DISTRICTS.

     HEAVY  INFRASTRUTURE  DAMAGE  HAS  BEEN REPORTED AND PRELIMINARY
  FIGURES  SHOW  AT  LEAST  3  PEOPLE DEAD AND A LARGE NUMBER WITHOUT
  SHELTER.

