<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 22 Aug 95 05:56:48 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Guyana: Chemical Spill  DHA-01



                INFORMATION REPORT NO.1 - GUYANA
                    CYANIDE MINE WASTE SPILL

1. A TAILINGS DAM AT THE OMAI GOLD MINE BREACHED ON SATURDAY
NIGHT, RELEASING UP TO 100,000 CUBIC METRES PER HOUR OF WASTE
CONTAINING CYANIDE.  THE TOXIC WASTE ENTERED THE OMAI RIVER
BEFORE FLOWING INTO THE ESSEQUIBO RIVER, THE MAJOR RIVER IN THE
COUNTRY WHICH IS A VITAL RESOURCE FOR DRINKING WATER AND FISHING.
THE PAN AMERICAN HEALTH ORGANIZATION (PAHO) REPORTS THAT CYANIDE
CONCENTRATIONS IN THE OMAI RIVER WAS 5.42 PPM AND RISING AS OF 21
AUGUST.  THE UNDP OFFICE REPORTS THAT AQUATIC LIFE IN THE OMAI
RIVER AND PARTS OF THE ESSE QUIBO RIVER HAVE BEEN SERIOUSLY
IMPACTED.

2. THE GUYANA GEOLOGY AND MINES COMMISSION DEFINED THE ACCIDENT
AS THE WORST INDUSTRIAL DISASTER TO HIT THE COUNTRY.  ALL MINING
OPERATIONS HAVE BEEN SHUT DOWN.

3. THE UNDP OFFICE REPORTS THAT ATTEMPTS ARE BEING MADE BY THE
CANADIAN OWNERS OF THE MINE TO STEM THE FLOW AND THAT COMMUNITIES
DOWN STREAM OF THE POLLUTION ARE BEING WARNED NOT TO USE WATER
FROM THE RIVER.  OFFICIALS HAVE BEEN DISTRIBUTING DRINKING WATER
TO AFFECTED COMMUNITIES, INCLUDING THE IMPORTANT TOWN OF BARTICA.

4. THE UNDP OFFICE REPORTS THAT THE NATIONAL RESPONSE TO THE
EMERGENCY IS BEING COORDINATED BY THE ADVISOR TO THE PRESIDENT ON
ENVIRONMENT, SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY, MR. NAVIN CHANDERPAL AND
MINISTER OF PUBLIC WORKS, MR. HARRIPERSAUD NOKTA.

5. NO SPECIFIC REQUEST FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE HAS YET BEEN
RECEIVED BY DHA.  THE ENVIRONMENTAL EMERGENCY RESPONSE
ORGANIZATIONS IN CANADA, UK AND USA HAVE BEEN INFORMED.

6. ENVIRONMENT CANADA REPORT THAT THEY ARE IN CONTACT WITH THEIR
EMBASSY IN GEORGETOWN AND ARE ASSESSING THE BEST COURSE OF
ACTION.

                  + DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS =

TELEPHONE NO: +41-22-917.12.34
EMERGENCY TEL. NO. (IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY): +41-22-917.20.10

DESK OFFICER: MR. GERARD LE CLAIRE DIRECT TEL: +41-22-917.11.73
PRESS TO CONTACT:  MRS.  MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:
+41-22-917.28.56

TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
