<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Wed, 20 Sep 95 07:24:34 EDT
Errors-To: disaster@vita.org
Reply-To: incident@lan.vita.org
Originator: sitreps@vita.org
Sender: sitreps@vita.org
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Laos: Floods  DHA-01
X-Listprocessor-Version: 6.0c -- ListProcessor by Anastasios Kotsikonas
X-Comment: Disaster/Emergency Reports for International Situations
X-Status: 


                              LAO PDR - FLOODS
                           INFORMATION REPORT NO.1
                              19 SEPTEMBER 1995

  SITUATION

  1.      TWO  MONTHS  OF  HEAVY MONSOON RAINS IN MEKONG RIVER BASIN,
  ASSOCIATED  WITH  A  SERIES  OF  TROPICAL  STORMS, HAVE RESULTED IN
  EXTENSIVE   FLOODS  IN  LARGE  PARTS  OF  LAO  PEOPLE'S  DEMOCRATIC
  REPUBLIC.

  2.      WIDESPREAD  FLOODING  OCCURRED  IN  VIENTIANE, BORIKHAMSAY,
  KHAMMOUANE,  SAVANNAKHET AND CHAMPASSAK PROVINCES, WITH  INUNDATION
  OF RIVERINE AREAS - THE COUNTRY'S BEST AGRICULTURAL LAND.

  3.     DUE TO LACK OF ACCURATE DATA, INFORMATION ON TOTAL DAMAGE IS
  INCOMPLETE.  VIRTUALLY  NO  INFORMATION  ON AFFECTED POPULATION HAS
  BEEN PROVIDED.

  4.      PRELIMINARY  REPORT  ON  ESTIMATES  OF DAMAGE TO CROP AREAS
  INDICATES  :  VIENTIANE  PREFECTURE  - 17,216HA CROP AREAS AFFECTED
  (ESTIMATED   LOSSES   14,392HA);   VIENTIANE  PROVINCE  -  12,036HA
  (7,611HA);  BORIKHAMSAY - 12,771HA (8,157HA); KHAMMOUANE - 17,378HA
  (13,546HA);  SAVANNAKHET  -  11,414HA  (8,432HA);  AND CHAMPASSAK -
  13,592HA (7,043HA).

  NATIONAL RESPONSE

  6.      GOVT  HAS  SO  FAR  ORGANIZED  3  ONE-DAY  FLOOD ASSESSMENT
  MISSIONS FOR REPRESENTATIVES FROM UN AND DONOR GOVERNMENTS.

  7.     ON 17 AUGUST, GOVT ISSUED EMERGENCY APPEAL FOR ASSISTANCE TO
  AVERT  FLOODING IN VIENTIANE. WITH LIMITED INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE
  (TOTALLING   SOME   USD  100,000),  GOVT  POSITIONED  SANDBAGS  AND
  REINFORCED CERTAIN AREAS OF THE MEKONG RIVERBANK IN VIENTIANE.

  8.     ON 7 SEPTEMBER, MINISTRY OF LABOUR AND SOCIAL WELFARE (MLSW)
  CALLED  FOR  IN-COUNTRY  DONATIONS FOR THE RELIEF OF FLOOD VICTIMS.
  MLSW  SET  UP COMMITTEES BOTH CENTRAL AND LOCAL LEVELS FOR THOROUGH
  DISTRIBUTION OF RELIEF AND MOBILIZING FUNDS AND DONATIONS.

  9.      ON  11  SEPTEMBER,  GOVT FORMALLY REQUESTED A JOINT FAO/WFP
  ASSESSMENT  TO  DETERMINE  CROP  LOSSES  AND  OTHER  DAMAGE  TO THE
  AGRICULTURAL SECTOR.

  10.     AS  YET,  GOVERNMENT  HAS  NOT  ISSUED  FORMAL  APPEAL  FOR
  INTERNATIONAL  RELIEF  ASSISTANCE  TO  OVERALL NUMBER OF VICTIMS OF
  FLOODS.

  INTERNATIONAL RESPONSE

  11.     ON  16 SEPTEMBER, DHA DISPATCHED UNDAC MISSION TO REINFORCE
  UN  RESIDENT  COORDINATOR  IN  VIENTIANE IN ASSESSING SITUATION AND
  IMMEDIATE  RELIEF NEEDS IN COOPERATION WITH REPRESENTATIVES OF FAO,
  WFP,  UNHCR,  WHO  AND  UNICEF,  UNDER THE AUTHORITY OF UN RESIDENT
  COORDINATOR.  THE TEAM IS CURRENTLY IN PROCESS OF FIELD ASSESSMENT.

  12.     LAO  RED  CROSS,  WITH  BRANCHES  IN  SOME  OF THE AFFECTED
  PROVINCES, IS PROVIDING SOME ASSISTANCE.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010
  DESK   OFFICER:    MR.   Y.   FUKASAWA,    DIRECT   TELEPHONE   NO.
  +41-22-917-3131
  PRESS    TO   CONTACT:   MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22--917-2856
