From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Bangladesh: Floods  DHA-13



                            BANGLADESH -- FLOODS
                    DHA GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO. 13
                               17 AUGUST 1995


  1.    DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE REPORTS THAT A UNDMT (UN DISASTER
MANAGEMENT  TEAM)  TASK  FORCE  MET  ON  16  AUGUST  TO  REVIEW  SITUATION.
REPRESENTED  WERE  DHA/UNDP,  UNICEF,  WFP,  WHO, BANGLADESH METEOROLOGICAL
DEPARTMENT,  AND  FLOOD  INFORMATION CENTER OF BANGLADESH WATER DEVELOPMENT
BOARD.

  2.      MONSOON ACTIVITY HAS BEEN HIGHER THAN USUAL DURING LAST 4-5
  DAYS  IN  BANGLADESH  AS  WELL AS IMMEDIATE CATCHMENT AREAS OF BOTH
  GANGES  AND  BRAHMAPUTRA  IN  INDIA.   HEAVY  RAINS  IN  ASSAM  AND
  MEGHALAYA  REGIONS  LED  TO  FLASH FLOODS IN GREATER SYLHET REGION,
  CAUSING LIMITED LOCALIZED DAMAGES.  BOTH GANGES AND BRAHMAPUTRA RUN
  ABOVE   DANGER   LEVEL   IN   VARIOUS   POINTS,   AND  MODERATE  TO
  HIGHER-THAN-AVERAGE FLOODING IS FEARED IN THE BASINS.

  3.      OVERALL  HEALTH  SITUATION IN FLOOD-HIT AREAS, PARTICULARLY
  DHAKA  AND  ITS  ADJOINING  LOW-LYING  AREAS,  IS  REPORTEDLY UNDER
  CONTROL.   WHO INFORMS THAT GOVT MADE PLAN OF ACTION TO PREPARE FOR
  THIRD  SPELL  OF  FLOODS.   GOVT ESTABLISHED TASK FORCE WITH WHO TO
  DEAL,  IN  COLLABORATION WITH NGO'S, WITH OUTBREAKS OF DIARRHOEA IN
  DHAKA.

  4.      UNDMT  TASK FORCE IS EXPECTED TO MEET AGAIN ON 21 AUGUST TO
  REVIEW  SITUATION,  AS  NEXT ONE WEEK IS CONSIDERED TO BE CRITICAL.
  DHA, THROUGH UNDP/DHA RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE, CONTINUES TO CLOSELY
  MONITOR SITUATION.


  TELEPHONE NO.   +41-22/917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TEL NO. +41-22/917.20.10

  DESK OFFICER:   MS. K. GOTOH, DIRECT TEL. +41-22/917.12.58
  PRESS   TO   CONTACT:    MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22/917.28.56

  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH
  FAX:  +41-22/917.00.23
