                    COMMONWEALTH OF DOMINICA  - HURRICANE
                        DHA-GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 1
                             12  SEPTEMBER 1995


  SITUATION

  1.       ON  5  SEPTEMBER  JUNE  1995  A  SEVERE  HURRICANE  CAUSED
  CONSIDERABLE DAMAGE TO THIS AND OTHER COUNTRIES IN THE REGION. THIS
  REPORT  IS  IN  ADDITION  TO  THE GLOBAL CARIBBEAN - HURRICANE LUIS
  SITUATION REPORTS.

  2.      CROP  DAMAGE  IN  THE  EAST  AND  THE  NORTH  ARE ESTIMATED
  BETWEEN  60  AND  100  PER  CENT  OF ALL CROP. MOSTLY AFFECTED WERE
  BANANA, PLANTAIN, AVOCADO AND CITRUS. THE FISHING INDUSTRY HAS BEEN
  AFFECTED IN SAN SAVEUR, FOND ST. JEAN AND ALONG THE WEST COAST.

  3.      HOUSES  WERE  DAMAGED  IN PORTSMOUTH, CASTLE BRUCE, VIEILLE
  CASE  AND  ANSE  SOLDAT.  ROADS WERE AFFECTED MAINLY ALONG THE WEST
  COAST BUT ALSO AT TOUCARIE. RESERVOIRS WERE DAMAGED.

  4.      ONE  PERSON  WAS  KILLED  AND  ONE SERIOUSLY INJURED BY THE
  HURRICANE.

  NATIONAL RESPONSE:

  5.      THE  GOVERNMENT  ESTIMATED  THAT   ALONE THE REHABILITATION
  WILL  COST  MILLIONS  OF  DOLLARS AND PROVIDED A PRELIMINARY DAMAGE
  ASSESSMENT  REPORT  TO  DHA GENEVA. FULL REPORT IS EXPECTED  WITHIN
  ONE WEEK.

  INTERNATIONAL  ASSISTANCE

  6.      THE  GOVERNMENT  OF  DOMINICA  REQUESTED  DHA TO APPEAL FOR
  INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE.

  7.      CONTRIBUTIONS REPORTED TO DHA-GENEVA
                                             

  UN SYSTEM                                            US DLRS

  DHA-GENEVA  EMERGENCY GRANT                       50,000


