Date: Fri, 28 Jul 95 06:58:41 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Bangladesh: Floods  DHA-10

                              BANGLADESH-FLOODS
                     DHA-GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO.10
                                28 JULY 1995


  1.    OVERALL  IMPROVEMENT  IN FLOOD SITUATION HAS BEEN REPORTED. DESPITE
HEAVY  RAINFALLS,  THE BRAHMAPUTRA IS RECEDING. THE GANGES IS ALSO RECEDING
IN  MANY  AREAS ALTHOUGH AT SOME POINTS THE RIVER IS STILL FLOWING SLIGHTLY
ABOVE DANGER LEVEL.

  2.     UNDP CONVENED A DONOR'S MEETING ON 24 JULY TO REVIEW ONGOING
  NATIONAL   RELIEF  OPERATION  AND  POSSIBILITY  OF  FUTURE  FLOODS.
  ATTENDANTS  WERE  GOVERNMENT  REPRESENTATIVES, UN AGENCIES AT FIELD
  LEVEL,  MAJOR  DONORS,  ASSOCIATION FOR DEVELOPMENT AGENCIES (ADAB)
  AND NGO DISASTER FORUM.

  3.      MEETING  WAS  INFORMED THAT GOVERNMENT IS CONTINUING RELIEF
  OPERATIONS.  NGOS ARE ALSO ACTIVELY INVOLVED AND INDICATED THE NEED
  FOR  INCREASED  ASSISTANCE.  GOVERNMENT  ADVISED THAT IT IS ABLE TO
  COPE WITH THE SITUATION WITH ITS OWN RESOURCES.

  4.      AS  FOR WATER LEVEL, GOVERNMENT INDICATED THAT A THIRD WAVE
  OF  FLOODS  IS  ANTICIPATED DURING THE SECOND WEEK OF AUGUST DUE TO
  EXPECTED HEAVY RAINFALL IN THE GANGES BASIN, EXPECTED ANOTHER WATER
  LEVEL  PEAK  IN THE BRAHMAPUTRA BASIN AND SPRING TIDE ON 10 AUGUST.
  THIS IS VERY LIKELY TO RESULT IN SYNCHRONIZATION OF THE TWO RIVERS.

  5.       UNDP  HAS FORMED A TASK FORCE COMPRISED OF WHO, UNICEF AND
  ADAB.  TASK  FORCE  WILL  WORK CLOSELY WITH GOVERNMENT TO DETERMINE
  LIKELY AREAS AND POPULATION TO BE AFFECTED BY THIRD WAVE OF FLOODS.

  6.      AS  YET,  NO  REQUEST FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE FROM THE
  GOVERNMENT  HAS  BEEN  RECEIVED.  DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE
  CONTINUES TO MONITOR SITUATION.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010
  DESK   OFFICER:    MR.   Y.   FUKASAWA,    DIRECT   TELEPHONE   NO.
  +41-22-917-3131
  PRESS    TO   CONTACT:   MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22--917-2856
