Date: Mon, 31 Jul 95 21:21:58 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Chile: Earthquake  DHA-01


                    CHILE - EARTHQUAKE IN NORTHERN REGION
                                30 JULY 1995
                                  12H00 UTC
                          INFORMATION REPORT NO. 1


  1.    AN  EARTHQUAKE MEASURING 7.8 ON THE RICHTER SCALE OCCURRED NEAR THE
NORTHERN  CHILE  CITY  OF ANTOFAGASTA (POPULATION APPROXIMATELY 228,000) AT
01.11 LOCAL TIME (05.11 UTC).

  2.      THE  CHILEAN  NATIONAL EMERGENCY OFFICE (ONEMI) REPORT THAT
  THE  EPICENTRE  WAS  AT  23.34S,  70.36W  -  SOME 20KM INTO THE SEA
  BETWEEN  ANTOFAGASTA AND MEJILLONES AT A DEPTH OF 33KM. THE INITIAL
  SHOCK LASTED FOR 90 SECONDS.

  3.      UP  TO  10  AFTERSHOCKS  HAVE  BEEN RECORDED WITH A MAXIMUM
  MAGNITUDE OF 6.1.

  4.     INITIAL ESTIMATES FROM THE CHILEAN NATIONAL EMERGENCY OFFICE
  INDICATE THAT 2 PEOPLE WERE KILLED AND 7 INJURED. SEVERAL BUILDINGS
  IN ANTOFAGASTA WERE DAMAGED. THE ELECTRICITY SUPPLY IN THE CITY WAS
  CUT  ALTHOUGH  THE  AUTHORITIES  REPORT  THAT  SUPPLIES  ARE  BEING
  RE-ESTABLISHED. THERE ARE REPORTS OF SIMILAR IMPACTS IN OTHER AREAS
  IN THE REGION.  DAMAGE ASSESSMENT SURVEYS ARE CONTINUING.

  5.     SWISS DISASTER RELIEF HAS OFFERED ASSISTANCE, ALTHOUGH THERE
  IS  NO  REPORT  OF  INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE BEING REQUIRED AT THIS
  TIME.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22- 917 12 34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: TEL NO. +41-22- 917 20 10

  DESK OFFICER: MR.GERARD LE CLAIRE , DIRECT TEL: +41-22- 917 11 73
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22-917-
  28. 56

  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22- 917. 00. 23
  INTERNET EMAIL: DHAGVA AT UN. ORG

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



