<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 1 Aug 95 04:36:06 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Bangladesh: Floods  DHA-11

                              BANGLADESH-FLOODS
                     DHA-GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO.11
                                31 JULY 1995


  1.   FLOOD SITUATION CONTINUES TO IMPROVE.

  2.      A  MEETING OF THE UNDMT TASK FORCE COMPRISING OF UNDP, WHO,
  UNICEF, WFP AND FAO WAS HELD ON 30 JULY TO MONITOR THE PROGNOSIS OF
  THE  IMPENDING THIRD SPELL OF FLOODS. REPRESENTATIVES OF BANGLADESH
  METEOROLOGICAL DEPARTMENT ALSO ATTENDED THE MEETING.

  3.      THE  POSSIBILITY  OF SYNCHRONIZATION OF THE BRAHMAPUTRA AND
  THE  GANGES  BASINS  STILL  CANNOT  BE DISMISSED. THE TASK FORCE IS
  CLOSELY  MONITORING  THE SITUATION AND WILL CONDUCT THE NEXT REVIEW
  OF THE SITUATION ON 6 AUGUST.

  4.      UK  GOVERNMENT  DECIDED  TO DONATE CASH GRANT OF USD 79,365
  (PDS STG 50,000) TO THE VICTIMS OF FLOOD IN BANGLADESH.

  5.      AS  YET,  NO  REQUEST FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE FROM THE
  GOVERNMENT  HAS  BEEN  RECEIVED.  DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE
  CONTINUES TO MONITOR SITUATION.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010
  DESK   OFFICER:    MR.   Y.   FUKASAWA,    DIRECT   TELEPHONE   NO.
  +41-22-917-3131
  PRESS    TO   CONTACT:   MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22--917-2856
  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



