Subject: Caribbean: Hurricane  DHA-02



                    CARIBBEAN-HURRICANE LUIS
                 ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA, DOMINICA,
                 ST. KITTS AND NEVIS, MONTSERRAT
                   DHA SITUATION REPORT NO. 2
                        7 SEPTEMBER 1995


1. IN WAKE OF HURRICANE LUIS, DAMAGE IS BEING REPORTED FROM
ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA, DOMINICA AND ST KITTS AND NEVIS.

2. GOVT OF ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA HAS REQUESTED DHA TO LAUNCH AN
APPEAL FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE.


ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA
===================
3. NO REPORT OF DEAD AND INJURED. WIDESPREAD IMPACT.
DAMAGE TO ROOF AND WALLS OF HOSPITAL, EXTENSIVE DAMAGE
TO HOUSING AND PUBLIC BUILDINGS. DISRUPTURE WATER AND
OF ELECTRICITY SUPPLY. TELECOMMUNICATIONS SYSTEMS
PARTIALLY OUT OF FUNCTION.

DOMINICA
==========
4. NO REPORT OF DEAD AND INJURED. DAMAGE TO BANANA CROP.
