<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Fri, 11 Aug 95 05:31:39 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Emergency Information Administrator)
Subject: China: Floods  DHA-01


                  CHINA - FLOODS IN NORTHEASTERN PROVINCES
                          INFORMATION REPORT NO. 1
                               10 AUGUST 1995
 

  1.     FROM  25  JULY   HEAVY  RAINS  HAVE  AFFECTED  LIAONING  AND JILIN
PROVINCES.THE  FAST  RISE  IN  WATER  LEVELS  IN ALL LARGE AND SMALL RIVERS
RESULTED  IN  THE  OVERFLOW OR BREACH OF EMBANKMENTS IN MANY PLACES IN BOTH
PROVINCES CAUSING VERY SERIOUS FLOODS.THE SITUATION REMAINS CRITICAL.

  2.     AS REPORTED BY THE GOVERNMENT 11.1 MILLION PEOPLE  HAVE BEEN
  AFFECTED  BY  THESE  FLOODS,2 MILLION PEOPLE WERE MAROONED BY FLOOD
  WATERS  AND  3.04  MILLION WERE EVACUATED TO SAFER PLACES BY RESCUE
  WORKERS.

  3.      IN  LIAONING PROVINCE MORE THAN 6 REGIONS WITH 9 CITIES, 39
  COUNTIES  AND  504 TOWNSHIPS  WITH A POPULATION OF 5.8 MILLION WERE
  SERIOUSLY  HIT  BY  THE  FLOODS.  IN  JILIN  PROVINCE 8 PREFECTURES
  (CITIES  OF  REGIONS), 32 COUNTIES, 296 TOWNSHIPS WITH A POPULATION
  OF 5,3 MILLION WERE SERIOUSLY AFFECTED.

  4.      IN  TOTAL  MORE THAN TWO MILLION ROOMS WERE DAMAGED AND ONE
  MILLION  ROOMS  WERE  DESTROYED. INFRASTRUCTURE FOR TRANSPORTATION,
  TELECOMMUNICATIONS,  ELECTRICAL  POWER  AND WATER SUPPLY AS WELL AS
  HOSPITALS AND SCHOOLS SUFFERED DAMAGE.

  5.     IN LIAONING 0.89 MILLION HECTARES OF CROPS WERE AFFECTED. IN
  BOTH PROVINCES 0.42 MILLION HEADS OF ANIMALS WERE REPORTED KILLED.

  6.      PREVIOUSLY  IN  MAY  CHINA  EXPERIENCED RAIN STORMS CAUSING
  SERIOUS  FLOODS AND HEAVY LOSSES AND DAMAGE IN PARTS OF TEN CENTRAL
  AND  SOUTHERN  PROVINCES  ALONG  THE  YANGTZE  RIVER  AFFECTING 100
  MILLION  PEOPLE.  THE  GOVERNMENT  DID NOT APPEAL FOR INTERNATIONAL
  ASSISTANCE.  FOR  FURTHER  DETAILS  SEE  INFORMATION REPORT DATED 7
  JULY.

  7.      THE PROVINCIAL PARTY AND GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS ARE DIRECTING
  THE ONGOING DISASTER RESPONSE SUPPORTED BY THE ARMY WORKING TO SAVE
  THE   EMBANKMENTS  AND  TO  EVACUATE  TRAPPED  PERSONS.  THE  LOCAL
  AUTHORITIES  HAVE  DISTRIBUTED  LARGE QUANTITIES OF FOOD, CLOTHING,
  DRINKING  WATER,  MEDICINE  AND  OTHER  RELIEF  ITEMS  AND  SET  UP
  TEMPORARY  SHELTERS  FOR  THE VICTIMS.THE MINISTRY OF CIVIL AFFAIRS
  HAS  SENT  A WORKING TEAM  HEADED BY THE VICE MINISTER TO GUIDE THE
  WORK. IT ALSO HAS SHIPPED 600 TENTS TO THE AREA.

  8.      DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT  REPRESENTATIVE  IN  BEIJING  IS CLOSELY
  FOLLOWING   UP   THE   SITUATION  WITH  THE  GOVERNMENT  DEPARTMENT
  RESPONSIBLE, THE MINISTRY OF CIVIL AFFAIRS.


  TELEPHONE NO: +4122-917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY TEL. NO.: +41-22-917.20.10

  DESK OFFICER: G. MORTIER, DIRECT TEL. +41-22-917.13.94
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22-917.2856

  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22-917.00.23
  INTERNET EMAIL: DHAGVA AT UN.ORG

  DPR 310 CHA
                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +


