<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Fri, 21 Jul 95 10:35:17 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Togo: Rains  DHA-02

                           TOGO - TORRENTIAL RAINS
                            SITUATION REPORT NO.2
                                21 JULY 1995




  1.    ACCORDING  TO  A  PRELIMINARY  REPORT  PREPARED  BY  A  UN  MISSION
(WHO,UNICEF,DHA/UNDP)  THE  FLASH  FLOODS  OF 3 AND 4 JULY AFFECTED 29 LOME
DISTRICTS  AND  RENDERED 75,000 PEOPLE HOMELESS, OF WHICH 71% ARE WOMEN AND
CHILDREN.



  2.     THE MOST AFFECTED DISTRICTS ARE :

  ADEWUI           BE                   KEGUE
  AFLAO-GAKALI     CASSABLANCA          KLIKAME
  AFLAO-TOTSI      CABEVITO             NOUVEAU ZONGO
  AGBALEPEDO       DOULASSAME           NOVISSI
  AKODESSEWA       DZIDZOLE             NOKAFU
  AKOSSOMBO        ELAVAGNON            NYEKONAKPOE
  AMOUTIEVE        FOREVER              TCKOIN-DOGBEAVOU
  ANCIEN ZONGO     GBADAGO              TCKOIN-TAME
  ATIKPA           GBEGNEDZI            WUITI
  AUBA             HANOUKOPE


  THE  TOTALITY  OF THE DISTRICTS DO NOT HAVE A PUBLIC SEWAGE SYSTEM,
  NO  RUNNING WATER, NO PUBLIC DRINKING-FOUNTAINS, NO ELECTRICITY AND
  NO  SANITATION  PUBLIC  SERVICE.  THE ABNORMAL RAIN FALL DURING THE
  MONTHS  OF  JUNE  AND JULY AGRAVATED BY THE INEFICIENCY OF THE CITY
  WATER  PUMPING  SYSTEM,  JUST ACCELERATED THE FLOODING OF THE ABOVE
  MENTIONED DISTRICTS.

  3.      THE  SANITARY  CONDITIONS  ARE EXTREMELY PRECARIOUS AND THE
  AUTHORITIES  FEAR  AN  OUTBREAK  OF ENDEMIC DISEASES. FROM 10 TO 17
  JULY  54 CASES OF SERIOUS DIARRHOEA WERE DETECTED, OF WHICH 26 WERE
  CONFIRMED.  6  PEOPLE  DIED. THE IDENTIFIED GERM IS A VIBRIO OF THE
  TYPE OGAWA.

  MOBIL  AND  REGULAR  MEDICAL TEAMS HAVE BEEN ORGANIZED BUT THEY ARE
  FACING  A  SERIOUS SHORTAGE OF MEDICINES, DISINFECTION PRODUCTS AND
  EQUIPMENT.

  4.     THE IMMEDIATE NEEDS IDENTIFIED CONCERN:

    REPAIRING OF THE MAIN WATER PUMPING STATIONS
    CLEARING OF THE MAIN GUTTERS AND RAIN WATER COLLECTORS
    ENSURING THE DISTRIBUTION OF DRINKING WATER TO THE VICTIMS
    DISINFECTION OF THE AFFECTED AREAS
    DISINFECTION OF THE WELLS DRINKING WATER
    FOOD
    MEDICINES AND MEDICAL SUPPLIES
    CLOTHES(FOR ADULTS AND CHILDREN)
    SHELTER/TENTS
    LOGISTICS FOR THE TEMPORARY RELOCATION OF THE VICTIMS


  5.      DHA  IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS CHANNEL FOR CASH CONTRIBUTIONS
  TO  BE  USED  DURING  IMMEDIATE  RELIEF  PHASE.  FUNDS ARE SPENT IN
  COORDINATION  WITH  RELEVANT  ORGANIZATIONS OF U.N. SYSTEM, AND DHA
  PROVIDES DONOR GOVERNMENTS WITH WRITTEN CONFIRMATION ON UTILIZATION
  OF FUNDS CONTRIBUTED.

  8.      FUNDS SHOULD BE TRANSFERRED TO DHA ACCOUNT NO. CO-590.160.1
  AT SWISS BANK CORPORATION, CASE POSTALE 2770,CH-1211 GENEVA 2, WITH
  REFERENCE: TOGO-TORRENTIAL RAINS, DHA-GENEVA.


  TELEPHONE NO. +41-22 917. 12. 34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: +41-22 917.20.10
  DESK OFFICER: MR. CARLOS PEREIRA, DIRECT TEL: +41-22 917.13.83
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22 917.28.56

  TELEX: 414242 DHA  CH
  FAX: +41-22 917.00.23
  INTERNET EMAIL:  DHAGVA AT UN. ORG

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



