<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 8 Aug 95 17:02:02 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Emergency Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Ukraine: Environmental  DHA-03
X-Status: 


                        UKRAINE - KHARKOV
                     ENVIRONMENTAL EMERGENCY
                      SITUATION REPORT NO.3
                          8 AUGUST 1995


1. UKRAINIAN AUTHORITIES CONTINUE THEIR EFFORTS TO IMPROVE LOCAL
PUMPING CAPACITY.  SOME OF THE PUMPS, RECEIVED THROUGH NATO AS
INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE, ARE STILL USED IN THE CITY OF KHARKOV.

2. AT THE END OF JULY, THE VOLUME OF UNTREATED SEWAGE WATERS
RELEASED INTO THE RIVERS LOPAN, UDY, KHARKIV AND THEN SEVERSKY
DONETS, REACHED 600,000 CUBIC METERS PER DAY.  NATIONAL
AUTHORITIES ARE TAKING MEASURES TO LIMIT AND STOP DISCHARGE OF
UNTREATED SEWAGE WATERS INTO RIVERS.  STEPS ARE ALSO TAKEN TO
IMPROVE RIVER WATER QUALITY BY USING AERATION AND HYDROLOGICAL
TECHNIQUES.

3. UKRAINIAN ENVIRONMENTAL AUTHORITIES HAVE FACED DIFFICULTIES IN
QUICK AND RELIABLE ASSESSMENT OF WATER POLLUTION, AND APPEALED
FOR URGENT FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO PURCHASE THE NECESSARY WATER
MONITORING EQUIPMENT.  FOLLOWING THIS REQUEST, DHA HAS RELEASED
AN EMERGENCY GRANT OF USD40,000 TO UKRAINE.

4. UKRAINIAN REQUEST FOR MEDICINES AND DISINFECTANTS IS STILL
GENERALLY VALID.  UNICEF IS SHIPPING URGENTLY FROM ITS COPENHAGEN
WAREHOUSE TO UKRAINE THE FOLLOWING SUPPLIES:

-  TETRACYCLINE 500,000 TABLETS
-  PEDIATRIC ERYTHROMYCIN SUSPENSION 3,000 BOTTLES (60ML EACH)
-  ORS - 125,000 PACKETS.

COUNTRIES AND ORGANIZATIONS WHICH HAVE ALREADY ASSISTED UKRAINE
WITH MEDICINES IN THIS PARTICULAR DISASTER, ARE ASKED TO INFORM
DHA IN ORDER TO AVOID DUPLICATION OF EFFORTS.


                  + DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS =

TELEPHONE NO: +41-22-917.12.34
EMERGENCY TEL. NO. (IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY): +41-22-917.20.10

DESK OFFICER: MR. VLADIMIR SAKHAROV DIRECT TEL: +41-22-917.11.42
PRESS TO CONTACT:  MRS.  MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:
+41-22-917.28.56

TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
FAX: +41-22-917.00.23
ELECTRONIC MAIL: DHAGVA AT UN.ORG

