<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Mon, 11 Sep 95 14:10:32 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Philippines: Floods  DHA-04


                      PHILIPPINES - FLOODS
                     INFORMATION REPORT NO.4
                        11 SEPTEMBER 1995

SITUATION
==========

1. UN RESIDENT COORDINATOR ISSUED CONSOLIDATED REPORT ON DAMAGE
CAUSED BY FLASHFLOOD WHICH HIT AREAS NEAR PARKER VOLCANO IN
MINDANAO ISLAND.

2. ON 6 SEPTEMBER, FLASHFLOOD INUNDATED 7 MUNICIPALITIES IN SOUTH
COTABATO PROVINCE AND 4 IN SULTAN KUDARAT PROVINCE.  POPULATION
AFFECTED IN TWO PROVINCES ARE:  IN SOUTH COTABATO - 15,563
PERSONS OR 3,052 FAMILIES, AND IN SULTAN KUDARAT - 8,915 PERSONS
OR 2,172 FAMILIES.  REPORTED CASUALTIES INCLUDE 48 DEAD, 7
INJURED AND 382 MISSING.

3. IN SOUTH COTABATO PROVINCE, ESTIMATED COST OF DAMAGE TO
BRIDGES, ROADS, AGRICULTURE, PRIVATE PROPERTY AND TRANSPORTATION
IS ABOUT USD 31.909 MILLION (PHP 327.2 MILLION).  DAMAGE TO 321
HOUSES WAS ALSO REPORTED.  IN SULTAN KUDARAT PROVINCE, ESTIMATED
COST OF DAMAGE TO BRIDGES, ROADS AND TRANSPORTATION IS ABOUT
USD 2.860 MILLION (PHP 72.7 MILLION).  DAMAGE TO 12,261 HA OF
AGRICULTURE AND 27 HOUSES WAS ALSO REPORTED.

NATIONAL RESPONSE
=====================

4. IN SOUTH COTABATO PROVINCE, 2,900 PERSONS OR 467 FAMILIES WERE
EVACUATED.  IN SULTAN KUDARAT PROVINCE, 1,050 PERSONS OR 262
FAMILIES WERE EVACUATED.  RESCUE AND RELIEF OPERATIONS ARE
ON-GOING.

5. A QUICK RESPONSE TEAM DISPATCHED BY THE PHILIPPINES INSTITUTE
OF VOLCANOLOGY AND SEISMOLOGY (PHIVOLCS) IS INVESTIGATING CAUSE
OF MASSIVE DISCHARGE OF FLOOD WATERS TO LOW-LYING AREAS.

6. IN THE ABSENCE OF DEFINITE INDICATORS FOR RENEWED VOLCANIC
ACTIVITY, PHIVOLCS REITERATES THAT PARKER VOLCANO HAS NOT ENTERED
ERUPTIVE PHASE.

7. NO INTERNATIONAL APPEAL HAS BEEN ISSUED BY THE GOVERNMENT.

            +UNITED NATIONS DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS+

TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234 IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:
TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010 DESK OFFICER:  MR.  Y. FUKASAWA,
DIRECT TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-3131
PRESS TO CONTACT:  MS.  M. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL.
+41-22--917-2856
TELEX:  414242 DHA CH
FAX: +41/22/9170023
INTERNET : E-MAIL.DHAGVA AT UN.ORG



