<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Fri, 21 Jul 95 12:45:30 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Bangladesh: Floods  DHA-09


                              BANGLADESH-FLOODS
                           INFORMATION REPORT NO.9
                                21 JULY 1995

  SITUATION

  1.      THE  OVERALL  SITUATION  IN  THE  FLOODED  AREA  AROUND THE
  BRAHMAPUTRA  BASIN (FROM CHILMARI TO ARICHA) IS IMPROVING. HOWEVER,
  THE  BRAHMAPUTRA  STILL CONTINUES TO FLOW ABOVE THE DANGER LEVEL AT
  ARICHA.

  2.      IN  THE GANGES BASIN, THE RIVERS ARE RISING STEADILY AT ALL
  POINTS  AS  EXPECTED  AND  CONTINUES  TO FLOW ABOVE DANGER LEVEL AT
  GOALUNDO AND BHAGYAKUL. AREAS DOWNSTREAM FROM GOALUNDO TO MADARIPUR
  HAVE  BEEN INUNDATED AND ARE EXPECTED TO REMAIN SO FOR THE NEXT FEW
  DAYS.

  3.      IN  THE  LOWER  PART OF THE MEGHNA BASIN, AREAS IN COMILLA,
  BRAHMANBARIA,  NARSINGDI,  MUNSHIGANJ,  NARAYANGANJ  AND  LOW LYING
  AREAS  OF  DHAKA  WERE  INUNDATED.  THE  SITUATION  HAS  STARTED TO
  IMPROVE;  HOWEVER, LOW LYING AREAS AROUND DHAKA AND NARAYANGANJ ARE
  EXPECTED  TO  REMAIN  INUNDATED  FOR  QUITE  SOME TIME AS THE WATER
  NORMALLY RECEDES AT A SLOWER PACE.

  4.      IT  HAS  BEEN  PROJECTED  BY  THE BANGLADESH METEOROLOGICAL
  DEPARTMENT  THAT  THE  NORTH-WESTERN  PART  OF THE GREATER RAJSHAHI
  DIVISION  IS  TO  EXPERIENCE  HEAVY  RAINFALLS DURING THE FIRST TWO
  WEEKS  OF  AUGUST.  NORMAL  MONSOON  IS EXPECTED IN THE BRAHMAPUTRA
  BASIN  IN  THE  NEXT  2-3  WEEKS. THE GOVERNMENT PREDICTED THAT THE
  BRAHMAPUTRA  IS  LIKELY  TO  EXPERIENCE ANOTHER PEAK AT BAHADURABAD
  DURING  THE  SECOND  WEEK  OF  AUGUST.  THIS IS LIKELY TO LEAD TO A
  SYNCHRONIZATION  WITH  HIGH  RIVER  LEVELS  IN THE GANGES FOR SHORT
  DURATION.

  NATIONAL RESPONSE

  5.      PRIME  MINISTER  SAID  THAT THE GOVERNMENT WILL PROVIDE THE
  FARMERS  WITH  SEEDLINGS  FREE OF COST AND HOUSE BUILDING GRANTS TO
  FLOOD  HIT  POOR  PEOPLE. GOVERNMENT WILL ALSO TAKE STEPS TO REPAIR
  THE  DAMAGED TUBEWELLS AND EMBANKMENTS THROUGHOUT THE STRUCK AREAS.
  RELIEF GOODS WERE DISTRIBUTED AMONG THE AFFECTED PEOPLE.

  6.      RELIEF  OPERATIONS  IN  DAMAGED  AREAS ARE STILL CONTINUING
  UNDER  THE  AEGIS OF THE MINISTRY OF DISASTER MANAGEMENT AND RELIEF
  IN  CONJUNCTION WITH THE BANGLADESH RED CRESCENT SOCIETY. NGOS HAVE
  ALSO GEARED UP THEIR RELIEF ACTIVITIES IN THE AFFECTED AREAS.

   7.     THE  ASSOCIATION FOR DEVELOPMENT AGENCIES (ADAB) CONVENED A
  MEETING TO REVIEW THE SITUATION. IT WAS REPORTED THAT THE EXTENT OF
  FLOODING  AND  FLOOD  DAMAGE  HAS LED TO THE WORST SITUATION IN THE
  LAST SEVERAL YEARS. ADAB AND THE NGO REPRESENTATIVES PRESENT AT THE
  MEETING  REQUESTED  DONORS TO COME FORWARD AND ASSIST NGOS IN THEIR
  RELIEF AND REHABILITATION EFFORT.

  8.      IN  VIEW  OF  THIS  SITUATION,  A LARGER DONOR COORDINATION
  MEETING  WILL  BE HELD ON 25 JULY TO APPRAISE DONORS OF THE OVERALL
  SITUATION  AS  WELL AS THE PROGNOSIS FOR THE REST OF THE VULNERABLE
  PERIOD OF THE MONSOON SEASON TILL THE END OF SEPTEMBER.

  9.      AS  YET,  NO  REQUEST FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE FROM THE
  GOVERNMENT  HAS  BEEN  RECEIVED.  DHA/UNDP  RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE
  CONTINUES TO MONITOR SITUATION.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010
  DESK   OFFICER:    MR.   Y.   FUKASAWA,    DIRECT   TELEPHONE   NO.
  +41-22-917-3131
  PRESS    TO   CONTACT:   MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22--917-2856
  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +


