<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 8 Aug 95 17:02:59 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Emergency Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Montserrat: Volcano  DHA-08
X-Status: 


                        MONTSERRAT- VOLCANIC ACTIVITY
                    DHA- GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO. 8
                                8 AUGUST 1995



  1.     REPORTS  INDICATE  INCREASING  SEISMIC  ACTIVITY,  AND  SCIENTISTS
MONITORING THE VOLCANO IN MONTSERRAT HAVE ADVISED A RAISING OF THE LEVEL OF
ALERT.

  2.     ON AUGUST 6, THE ELDERLY AND SICK FROM THE VILLAGES NEAR THE
  VOLCANO  WERE  EVACUATED  TO  TENT VILLAGES ALREADY IN PLACE IN THE
  NORTH OF THE ISLAND.

  3.       ON  AUGUST  7, LOCAL AUTHORITIES STARTED THE EVACUATION OF
  THE  ELDERLY  AND  SICK  FROM  THE  SOUTH,  INCLUDING THE MAIN TOWN
  PLYMOUTH.  VILLAGES ON THE EASTERN PART ARE ALSO BEING EVACUATED TO
  THE NORTH.

  4.      ACCORDING  TO  THE REGIONAL DELEGATION OF THE INTERNATIONAL
  FEDERATION  OF  RED  CROSS AND RED CRESCENT SOCIETIES, AN ESTIMATED
  1,500 PEOPLE HAVE ALREADY LEFT THE ISLAND.

  5.      THE  UNITED  KINGDOM HAS PROVIDED THREE C-130 PLANES LOADED
  WITH  EMERGENCY  SUPPLIES FOR THE EVACUATED POPULATION CONCENTRATED
  IN THE NORTH OF THE ISLAND.

  6.      LOCAL  AUTHORITIES,  THROUGH  THE  GOVERNOR  AND  THE CHIEF
  MINISTER  OF  MONTSERRAT  CONTINUE  TO  BRIEF THE POPULATION ON THE
  PRECAUTIONARY ACTIONS BEING TAKEN.

  6.     THE REGIONAL RESPONSE MECHANISM REMAINS ON ALERT.

  TELEPHONE NO: +41-22-917-1234

  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE +41-22-917-2010

  DESK OFFICER: CARLOS PEREIRA, DIRECT TEL: +41-22-917-13 83
  PRESS TO CONTACT:  MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, TEL: +4-22-917-28-56

  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22-917-0023
  ELECTRONIC MAIL: INTERNET DHA GVA AT UN.ORG

