<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Mon, 21 Aug 95 06:41:14 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Morocco: Floods  DHA-01


                        MOROCCO - FLOODS
                   DHA INFORMATION REPORT NO 1
                         20 AUGUST 1995

1. FLASH FLOODS KILLED MORE THAN 100 PEOPLE AND CAUSED
DAMAGE TO HOMES AND INFRASTRUCTURE IN THE SOUTHWEST
OF MOROCCO, FOLLOWING TORRENTIAL RAINS WHICH HIT THE
ATLAS MOUNTAIN RANGE ON THURSDAY 17 AUGUST. INFORMATION ON
CASUALTIES AND DAMAGE IS STILL PRELIMINARY AS GOVERNMENT
ASSESSES, AND RESPONDS, TO THE EMERGENCY. SOME PEOPLE ARE
FEARED MISSING IN AREAS TO WHICH ACCESS HAS BEEN CUT BY
THE FLOODS. MEDIA REPORTS WORST HIT AREA TO BE SITUATED
JUST SOUTH MARRAKESH.

2. DHA, IN CLOSE CONTACT WITH THE UNITED NATIONS
RESIDENT COORDINATOR IN RABAT, IS MONITORING
THE SITUATION AS MORE INFORMATION BECOMES AVAILABLE.

3. NO REQUEST FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE HAS BEEN
RECEIVED BY DHA AS AT 20 AUGUST 1995.

    + UNITED NATIONS DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS+

