Date: Wed, 6 Sep 95 17:27:17 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Philippines: Floods  DHA-02



                            PHILIPPINES - FLOODS
                           INFORMATION REPORT NO.2
                              6 SEPTEMBER 1995


  1.    UPDATED  REPORT  ON  DAMAGE  CAUSED  BY  TORRENTIAL RAINS CAUSED BY
TYPHOON  GENING  (INTERNATIONAL  CODE  NAME  KENT) INDICATES THAT NUMBER OF
PERSONS  AFFECTED  IN REGIONS I, II, III, IV, V AND NATIONAL CAPITAL REGION
(METRO MANILA) TOTALLED 195,886 OR 39,358 FAMILIES. CASUALTIES TOTALLED 6.

  2.      IN  ILOCOS  NORTE  PROVINCE,  DAMAGE  TO INFRASTRUCTURE AND
  AGRICULTURE INCREASED TO ABOUT USD 351,000 (P 8.916 MILLION).

  3.      IN  BATANES  PROVINCE,  DAMAGE TO CROPS, INFRASTRUCTURE AND
  PRIVATE  PROPERTIES  AMOUNTED  TO  ABOUT  USD  3,078,000  (P 78.187
  MILLION).

  4.     IN BACOLOR TOWN IN PAMPANGA PROVINCE, 500 HOUSES WERE BURIED
  UNDER  A LAHAR FROM 4 TO 5 FEET DEEP. THREE SCHOOLS, PUBLIC MARKET,
  WATER  WORKS, CHURCH AND ROADS WERE DAMAGED. IN FLORIDA BLANCA TOWN
  ALSO  IN  PAMPANGA,  EARTH  DIKES,  SPUR DIKES AND SANDBAGGING WERE
  PARTIALLY  WASHED  OUT  OR  ERODED. DAMAGE TO CROPS, LIVESTOCKS AND
  INFRASTRUCTURE AMOUNTED TO ABOUT USD 379,000 (P 9.636 MILLION).

  5.     IN BATAAN PROVINCE, DAMAGE TO INFRASTRUCTURE AND AGRICULTURE
  AMOUNTED TO ABOUT USD 3,249,000 (P 82.537 MILLION).
  6.      AS  YET,  NO  INTERNATIONAL  APPEAL  HAS BEEN ISSUED BY THE
  GOVERNMENT.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-1234
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22-917-2010
  DESK   OFFICER:    MR.   Y.   FUKASAWA,    DIRECT   TELEPHONE   NO.
  +41-22-917-3131
  PRESS    TO   CONTACT:   MS.   M.   MOULIN-ACEVEDO,   DIRECT   TEL.
  +41-22--917-2856
  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH
