<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
X-To: newinfo
Sender: sitreps@vita.org
Subject: Russian Federation: Chechnya  DHA (Aug-95)
X-listprocessor-version: 6.0c -- ListProcessor by Anastasios Kotsikonas
X-comment: Disaster/Emergency Reports for International Situations
Originator: sitreps@vita.org
Date: Wed, 20 Sep 95 09:54:56 EDT
X-Status: 

            UNITED NATIONS INTER-AGENCY HUMANITARIAN PROGRAMME
                 FOR PERSONS DISPLACED AS A RESULT OF THE
                     EMERGENCY SITUATION IN CHECHNYA,
                            RUSSIAN FEDERATION

                  SITUATION REPORT OF THE DHA COORDINATOR
              BASED ON FIELD REPORTS AND COVERING THE PERIOD
                          28 JULY-31 AUGUST 1995
 

    GENERAL

  A  MILITARY  AGREEMENT  SIGNED  ON  30 JULY 1995 IS GENERALLY BEING
  RESPECTED,  ALTHOUGH  NUMEROUS  INCIDENTS  HAVE BEEN REPORTED.  THE
  AGREEMENT  PROVIDED  FOR  DISARMAMENT  OF  THE CHECHEN FIGHTERS AND
  WITHDRAWAL OF RUSSIAN FEDERAL FORCES.  CHECHEN FIGHTERS HAVE HANDED
  IN  A QUANTITY OF LIGHT WEAPONS AND THE FIRST WITHDRAWAL OF RUSSIAN
  FORCES,  FROM THE VILLAGE OF ASSINOVSKAYA, HAS COMMENCED.  EXCHANGE
  OF PRISONERS HAS NOT YET STARTED.

  THE  POLITICAL  AGREEMENT  ON  THE  FUTURE  OF  CHECHNYA, WHICH WAS
  SUPPOSED  TO  FOLLOW  THE  MILITARY  AGREEMENT,  HAS  NOT  YET BEEN
  REACHED.   PRESIDENT  YELTSIN  HAS  APPOINTED  THE SECRETARY OF THE
  NATIONAL  SECURITY COUNCIL, MR. OLEG LOBOV, AS SPECIAL PRESIDENTIAL
  ENVOY TO CHECHNYA WITH THE TASK OF OVERSEEING THE IMPLEMENTATION OF
  THE MILITARY AGREEMENT AND STABILISING THE SITUATION.  HE WILL HAVE
  FULL  POWERS  OVER  ALL  OTHER  FEDERAL  AUTHORITIES  IN  THE AREA.
  PRESIDENT  YELTSIN  HAS  ALSO  EXPRESSED WILLINGNESS TO PARTICIPATE
  PERSONALLY IN NEGOTIATIONS, AT AN APPROPRIATE TIME.

  IN  SPITE  OF  THE CEASE-FIRE CALLED FOR BY THE MILITARY AGREEMENT,
  REPEATED   SHELLING   WAS  HEARD  BY  UN  STAFF  IN  SLEPTSOVSKAYA,
  INGUSHETIA  WHILE  SHELLING  AND  FIRING  WAS HEARD COMING FROM THE
  DIRECTION OF BAMUT, IN SOUTHWEST CHECHNYA, NEAR THE INGUSH BORDER.

  IN  DAGHESTAN,  FOUR  BORDER  GUARDS  AND  EIGHT DAGHESTANI SPECIAL
  POLICE   ("OMON")   WERE  REPORTEDLY  KILLED  BY  CHECHEN  FIGHTERS
  ATTEMPTING TO CROSS THE BORDER INTO BOTLIKH.

  TWO  CHILDREN  WERE  INJURED AND ONE KILLED BY MINE EXPLOSIONS NEAR
  THE VILLAGE OF SHUSHA, IN THE BORDER AREA.

  THE  QUESTION OF HANDING IN ARMS IS OF PARTICULAR IMPORTANCE TO THE
  UNITED  NATIONS  IN  THE SERNOVODSKAYA AREA OF INGUSHETIA, WHERE UN
  HUMANITARIAN  RELIEF IS BEING PROVIDED.  THE AREA IS MARKED ON MAPS
  AS BEING PART OF INGUSHETIA; ITS POPULATION IS LARGELY CHECHEN, AND
  APPARENTLY    BOTH   THE   INGUSH   GOVERNMENT  AND  THE  TEMPORARY
  ADMINISTRATION  IN CHECHNYA HAVE AGREED THAT THE AREA SHOULD REVERT
  TO CHECHNYA.  THE CHECHEN FLAG WAS RECENTLY RAISED IN ASSINOVSKAYA,
  AND  CHECHEN  FIGHTERS,  WHO  HAVE  FREQUENTLY SOUGHT REFUGE IN THE
  AREA, STILL HAVE THEIR WEAPONS.

  INSIDE  CHECHNYA,  IT HAS BEEN REPORTED THAT 244 LIGHT WEAPONS, BUT
  NO  HEAVY WEAPONS, HAVE BEEN HANDED IN BY CHECHEN FIGHTERS.  IT WAS
  ALSO REPORTED THAT THE CITY OF GROZNY IS NOW FULL OF ACTIVITY.

  ARMED  MEN  BROKE  INTO  THE  ICRC OFFICE IN KHASAVYURT (DAGHESTAN)
  DURING THE REPORTING PERIOD AND STOLE EVERYTHING, INCLUDING MEDICAL
  SUPPLIES  AND  SATELLITE RADIO EQUIPMENT.  UNKNOWN PERSONS FIRED AN
  ANTI-TANK  GRENADE  AT  THE  RESIDENCE  OF  THE  PRIME  MINISTER OF
  DAGHESTAN; NO CASUALTIES WERE REPORTED.

  UNHCR  MOVED  ITS  OFFICE  TO  MORE SECURE PREMISES IN MAKHACHKALA,
  WHICH  WILL  ALSO  ACCOMMODATE  WFP  AND  A UNICEF EXPERT IN TRAUMA
  RELIEF.   EXCEPT  FOR  THIS ONE CONTINUING ACTIVITY, UNICEF HAS NOW
  COMPLETED ITS PROGRAMME IN DAGHESTAN.

  AN  AUDIT  OF  THE  UNHCR  OFFICE IN MAKHACHKALA WAS CARRIED OUT BY
  UNITED NATIONS EXTERNAL AUDITORS.


  TARGET POPULATION

  A  DHA/UNHCR  MISSION  WHICH  VISITED INGUSHETIA, NORTH OSSETIA AND
  DAGHESTAN FROM 12 TO 20 AUGUST CONCLUDED THAT THE PRESENT NUMBER OF
  IDPS  IN  INGUSHETIA  WAS 67,000; IN NORTH OSSETIA THERE WERE 5,000
  WHILE  IN  DAGHESTAN THERE WERE 50,000.  IT WAS THUS ESTIMATED THAT
  THE  TOTAL  NUMBER  OF  IDPS  WAS  122,000.   IT WAS NOTED THAT, IN
  ADDITION  TO  THIS,  THERE  WERE 32,000 IDPS IN INGUSHETIA FROM THE
  PRIGORODNY  DISTRICT  OF  NORTH  OSSETIA,  AND 35,000 REFUGEES FROM
  GEORGIA IN NORTH OSSETIA.

  IT  SHOULD BE NOTED THAT A SURVEY OF BENEFICIARIES IN INGUSHETIA BY
  UNHCR FIELD STAFF IS STILL UNDER WAY.

  THERE  HAS BEEN A SIGNIFICANT NUMBER OF RETURNS IN RECENT WEEKS; IN
  THE  UPDATE  TO THE UNITED NATIONS CONSOLIDATED INTER-AGENCY APPEAL
  FOR  PERSONS  DISPLACED  AS  A RESULT OF THE EMERGENCY SITUATION IN
  CHECHNYA,  IT  WAS  ESTIMATED  THAT  THE  TOTAL  NUMBER  OF IDPS IN
  INGUSHETIA, NORTH OSSETIA AND DAGHESTAN WAS 175,000.

  IN  INGUSHETIA,  NEW  CRITERIA  HAVE  BEEN ESTABLISHED BY THE LOCAL
  MIGRATION  SERVICE  FOR  RECOGNITION  AS  AN IDP;  THESE CONDITIONS
  INCLUDE PROOF OF PROPERTY DESTRUCTION IN CHECHNYA.

  THE  DAGHESTAN  MIGRATION  SERVICE HAS RECEIVED AN INSTRUCTION FROM
  THE  FEDERAL  MIGRATION  SERVICE TO CONSIDER GRANTING THE STATUS OF
  "FORCED  MIGRANT"  TO  SELECTED  IDPS,  WHO  REPORTEDLY  MUST BE OF
  DAGHESTANI BACKGROUND TO QUALITY.


  INTER-AGENCY COORDINATION

  AS  MENTIONED  ABOVE, A DHA/UNHCR MISSION VISITED INGUSHETIA, NORTH
  OSSETIA  AND  DAGHESTAN  FROM  12 TO 20 AUGUST 1995 AND CONDUCTED A
  REVIEW  OF  THE PROGRAMME ON THE BASIS OF INTER-AGENCY DISCUSSIONS.
  THE RESULTS OF THIS REVIEW WILL BE COMMUNICATED TO THE INTER-AGENCY
  NIS  TASK  FORCE  AND  TO  A DONORS MEETING WHICH WILL BE HELD ON 4
  OCTOBER IN GENEVA.

  UNICEF CLOSED ITS OFFICE IN MAKHACHKALA AT THE END OF AUGUST, AFTER
  COMPLETING   ITS  DISTRIBUTION  OF  UNICEF  RELIEF  SUPPLIES.  (THE
  DISTRIBUTION OF CHILDREN'S FOOTWEAR WILL BE HANDLED BY UNHCR.)  THE
  UNICEF EXPERT IN TRAUMA RELIEF REMAINS IN PLACE.

  IOM  ALSO  CLOSED ITS OFFICE IN DAGHESTAN AT THE END OF AUGUST, AND
  WILL NOW CONCENTRATE ITS EFFORTS INSIDE CHECHNYA.

  ICRC  ANNOUNCED  THE  ARRIVAL OF SCHOOL MATERIALS WHICH ADDRESS THE
  TOPIC  OF WAR AND PEACE TO ENHANCE RESPECT FOR HUMANITARIAN LAW AND
  HUMAN RIGHTS.


  PROGRAMME DELIVERY

  SHELTER

  UNHCR  HAS  SIGNED  AN  AGREEMENT WITH RELIEF INTERNATIONAL FOR THE
  PROCUREMENT  OF  120  PREFABRICATED  UNITS AND RELATED SANITARY AND
  UTILITY WORK AT SIX SITES.


  WAR AND SANITATION

  PROCUREMENT  OF  SIX  SEWAGE  TRUCKS  IS  UNDER  WAY,  FOR  USE  IN
  INGUSHETIA   AND  DAGHESTAN.   IN  THE  LATTER  REPUBLIC,  TWO  NEW
  CONTRACTS FOR SEWAGE SYSTEMS AND WATER SUPPLY HAVE BEEN SIGNED.


  DOMESTIC ITEMS

  DELIVERIES  OF BLANKETS, MATTRESSES, PLASTIC CANS, SUMMER SHOES AND
  PLASTIC SHEETS TO IDPS IN INGUSHETIA ARE CONTINUING. PROCUREMENT OF
  WINTER JACKETS AND SHOES IS UNDER WAY.


  FOOD

  IN  INGUSHETIA AND NORTH OSSETIA THE FIRST ROUND OF WHEAT FLOUR HAS
  BEEN  COMPLETED,  WITH  473 MTS DISTRIBUTED THROUGH 34 DISTRIBUTION
  POINTS.   THE SECOND ROUND IS NOW UNDERWAY; THE TOTAL QUANTITY WILL
  BE 1,800 MTS.

  75  MTS OF SUGAR HAVE BEEN RECEIVED IN VLADIKAVKAZ AND DISTRIBUTION
  WILL COMMENCE SHORTLY.

  THE  FIRST  THREE OUT OF FIVE RAILWAY WAGONS CARRYING VEGETABLE OIL
  HAVE  REACHED  VLADIKAVKAZ;  THE ARRIVAL  OF THE REMAINING TWO WILL
  MEAN  THAT  ALL SUPPLIES FOR THE PRESENT PHASE OF THE OPERATION  --
  THAT  IS,  NOT  COUNTING  THE  WINTER  PROGRAMME  -- WILL HAVE BEEN
  RECEIVED.

  IN  DAGHESTAN,  40  MTS OF SUGAR ARRIVED AFTER TWO WEEKS OF CUSTOMS
  DELAY  ON THE UKRAINIAN-RUSSIAN BORDER.  THE FIRST DISTRIBUTION OUT
  OF  1,200  MTS  OF  WHEAT  FLOUR HAS BEEN COMPLETED, AND THE SECOND
  COMMENCED WITH SIMULTANEOUS DISTRIBUTION OF SUGAR.

  95  MTS OF VEGETABLE OIL REACHED DAGHESTAN ON 4 SEPTEMBER AFTER THE
  WFP REPRESENTATIVE HAD TRAVELLED TO NOVOROSSIISK PORT WITH A CONVOY
  TO  DEAL  WITH  CUSTOMS  PROBLEMS.  5  MTS WERE DAMAGED AT SEA AS A
  RESULT OF INCORRECT LOADING.

  THERE IS STILL AN URGENT NEED FOR CONTRIBUTIONS FOR WINTER FOOD.


  HEALTH

  UNICEF  MEDICAL  SUPPLIES  RECEIVED  BY  AIR ON 11 AUGUST HAVE BEEN
  DELIVERED TO NAZRAN HOSPITAL IN INGUSHETIA.


    COMMUNITY SERVICES

    A PRIMARY EDUCATION PROJECT WILL BE IMPLEMENTED IN DAGHESTAN WHEN
    THE SCHOOL YEAR STARTS, WITH NGO EQUILIBRE AS THE IMPLEMENTING
    PARTNER.  IDP CHILDREN NOT ATTENDING LOCAL SCHOOLS WILL BE
    SUPERVISED BY IDP EDUCATION COMMITTEE AND TAUGHT BY 20 IDP
    TEACHERS.  UNHCR WILL PROVIDE ONE VEHICLE, WHILE UNICEF IS
    FINANCING EDUCATIONAL MATERIALS AND SUPPLIES.  A UNICEF SURVEY
    FOUND GREAT CONCERN AMONG PARENTS FOR THE EDUCATION OF THEIR
    CHILDREN.  IN INGUSHETIA, SCHOOL TEACHING HAS STARTED IN FIVE
    COLLECTIVE CENTRES.  IN AUGUST, 700 IDP CHILDREN TOOK PART IN
    SUMMER SCHOOL ACTIVITIES IN 40 COLLECTIVE CENTRES.

    IN AKI-YURT (INGUSHETIA) THE IDP WOMEN'S GROUP HAS COMMENCED
    MANUFACTURE OF CLOTHES FOR 52 CHILDREN, UNDER AN AGREEMENT WITH
    UNHCR.

    THE UNICEF TRAUMA RELIEF EXPERT GAVE A SEMINAR IN SERNOVODSKAYA
    (INGUSHETIA) TO TRAIN LOCAL PEOPLE.  IT IS ESTIMATED THAT THE
    TRAINED PERSONS IN TURN WILL REACH 4,000 IDPS.


  =====================================
  UNITED NATIONS OFFICE IN THE
  RUSSIAN FEDERATION - MOSCOW

  MR. CHRISTOPHER CARPENTER
  TEL.: (7 095) 284.3220/973.1893
  FAX:  (7 095)  973.1960

  COMPLEX EMERGENCY DIVISION
  (CED) - NEW YORK
  MR. GERHARD PUTMAN-CRAMER
  TEL.: (1 212) 963.2406
  FAX:  (1 212) 963.1312

  COMPLEX EMERGENCY SUPPORT UNIT
  (CESU)- Geneva
  MR. PAUL HEBERT / MS. KATARINA TOLL
  TEL.: (41 22) 788.6381 / 788.7021
  FAX:  (41 22) 788.6386 / 788.6387

  PRESS TO CONTACT: MS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO
