<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 19 Sep 95 12:40:54 EDT
Errors-To: disaster@vita.org
Reply-To: incident@lan.vita.org
Originator: sitreps@vita.org
Sender: sitreps@vita.org
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Dominica: Hurricane  DHA-03
X-Listprocessor-Version: 6.0c -- ListProcessor by Anastasios Kotsikonas
X-Comment: Disaster/Emergency Reports for International Situations
X-Status: 



                 COMMONWEALTH OF DOMINICA  - HURRICANE LUIS
                        DHA-GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 3
                             19  SEPTEMBER 1995


  SITUATION


  1.     FROM  NIGHTFALL MONDAY 4 TO ABOUT MIDDAY TUESDAY 5 SEPTEMBER
  HURRICANE  LUIS  LASHED  DOMINICA  WITH HEAVY WINDS, ACCOMPANIED BY
  HEAVY  RAINFALL  AND EXTREMELY HIGH WAVES FOR NEARLY 18 HOURS. THIS
  REPORT  IS  IN  ADDITION  TO  THE GLOBAL CARIBBEAN - HURRICANE LUIS
  SITUATION REPORTS.

  2.      ASSESSMENT  GIVEN BY THE OFFICE OF DISASTER PREPAREDNESS OF
  THE GOVERNMENT OF THE COMMONWEALTH OF DOMINICA ESTIMATE THE COST OF
  REHABILITATION  OF  EC$  127,730,000   (1  EC$ = US$ 2.7) EXCLUDING
  DAMAGE TO THE PUBLIC UTILITY SERVICES. THE REPORT IS AVAILABLE WITH
  THE  DHA  DESK  ON REQUEST. SO FAR NO GOVERNMENT REPORT RECEIVED ON
  HURRICANE  MARILYN  BUT  THE  UN  INTERAGENCY ASSESSMENT TEAM CDERA
  REPORTED OF HUNDREDS OF HOUSES DAMAGED.

  3.      THE  UNUSUAL HEAVY SEAS DAMAGED COASTAL DEFENCE STRUCTURES,
  PORTS,  HARBOURS  AND  BEACHES,  RESULTING IN WIDE-SPREAD DAMAGE TO
  COASTAL  ROADS,  RIVERS  OVERFLOWING  DAMAGED  BRIDGES. RAIN CAUSED
  INNUMERABLE LANDSLIDES BLOCKING BOTH MAIN AND FEEDER ROADS. VILLAGE
  WATER  SYSTEMS  WERE  CUT,  POWER  SHUT  DOWN  RADIO, AND TELEPHONE
  COMMUNICATIONS  WERE  INTERRUPTED.   A  SMALL NUMBER OF HOUSES (80)
  WERE  DAMAGED  OR  DESTROYED  BUT  MAJOR DAMAGE WAS REPORTED ON ONE
  HOTEL IN PORTSMOUTH AND FIVE HOTELS IN ROSEAU.

  4.     AGRICULTURE: 90 PER CENT OF  BANANA ACREAGE WAS KNOCKED DOWN
  AND  50 PER CENT OF TREE CROP PRODUCTION WAS DESTROYED. OTHER CROPS
  LIKE  CITRUS,  AVOCADO, PLANTAIN, BREADFRUIT, ANTHURIUM AND PASSION
  FRUIT  SUFFERED  LOSSES  UP TO 80 PER CENT.  IN TOTAL  A PRODUCTION
  LOSS  OF  EC$  25,891,928  IS ESTIMATED. IN  ADDITION LOSSES PARTLY
  STILL  TO  BE  ASSESSED  OCCURRED  IN  THE  SECTORS  OF  LIVESTOCK,
  FISHERIES, FORESTRY AND ENVIRONMENT.

  5.      TWO  DEATHS  WERE REPORTED AND OTHER PERSONS WERE SERIOUSLY
  INJURED.

  REGIONAL ACTION

  6.      INTER-AGENCY  TEAM  (CDERA,  CARIBBEAN DISASTER RELIEF UNIT
  (CDRU),  UNDP/DHA  RESIDENT  COORDINATOR AND PAHO) IS ASSESSING THE
  SITUATION  IN  THE  REGION.  EASTERN  CARIBBEAN DONOR GROUP MEETING
  REGULARLY  IN  BARBADOS  UNDER  CHAIRMANSHIP  OF  UNDP/DHA RESIDENT
  COORDINATOR.

  NATIONAL RESPONSE

  7.     THE GOVERNMENT ASSESSED THE DAMAGE AND  PREPARED A PROGRAMME
  FOR RECONSTRUCTION OF INFRASTRUCTURE AND REHABILITATION OF AFFECTED
  SECTORS INCLUDING AN EMERGENCY ACTION PROGRAMME FOR THE AGRICULTURE
  WORTH  EC$15.2 MIO. ALONE. THE ESTIMATATION  FOR REHABILITATION AND
  RECONSTRUCTION  COULD  APPROACH  ABOUT  EC$  175  FOR  ALL AFFECTED
  SECTORS.  THE  PERMANENT  MISSION  IN GENEVA IS IN CONSTANT CONTACT
  WITH DHA.

  NEEDS IN INTERNATIONAL  ASSISTANCE (IDENTIFIED)

  8.     US$ 100,000 FOR SCHOOL REHABILITATION.  TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE
  TO PREPARE A PROPOSAL FOR THE REHABILITATION OF COASTAL AREAS.

  CONTRIBUTIONS REPORTED TO DHA-GENEVA
                                   

  9.     UN SYSTEM                                     US DRLS

  DHA-GENEVA  EMERGENCY GRANT                       50,000

  10.    DHA IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS A CHANNEL FOR CASH CONTRIBUTIONS
  TO  BE  USED  DURING  IMMEDIATE  RELIEF  PHASE.  FUNDS ARE SPENT IN
  COORDINATION  WITH  RELEVANT  ORGANIZATIONS  OF  THE UN SYSTEM, DHA
  PROVIDES DONOR GOVERNMENTS WITH WRITTEN CONFIRMATION OF UTILIZATION
  OF FUNDS CONTRIBUTED.

  11.     DHA  PISA  WAREHOUSE  CAN  BE USED AS AN ASSEMBLY POINT FOR
  SHIPMENTS,  TO  AFFECTED  AREA,  WHETHER  GOODS  COME DIRECTLY FROM
  DONORS OR FROM OTHER WAREHOUSES.

  12.     TRANSFERS  OF  FUNDS  SHOULD  BE MADE TO DHA ACCOUNT NUMBER
  CO-590.160.1  AT  SWISS  BANK  CORPORATION, CASE POSTALE 2770, CH -
  1211  GENEVA  2,  WITH  FOLLOWING  REFERENCE:  DOMINICA - HURRICANE
  LUIS, DHA-GENEVA.

  13.     FOR  COORDINATION  PURPOSES, DONORS ARE REQUESTED TO INFORM
  DHA-GENEVA,  AS  INDICATED  BELOW,  OF  BILATERAL  RELIEF  MISSION,
  PLEDGES, CONTRIBUTIONS AND THEIR CORRESPONDING VALUE BY ITEM.

  TELEPHONE NO.   +41-22/917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TEL NO. +41-22/917.20.10
  DESK OFFICER:   Mr. GERHARD MORTIER  DIRECT TEL. +41-22/917.13.94.
  PRESS TO CONTACT:  MS. M. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL.
   +41-22/917.28.56
  TELEX:  414242 DHA CH
  FAX:  +41-22/917.00.23
  ELECTRONIC MAIL:  INTERNET DHAGVA AT UN. ORG
