<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 1 Aug 95 04:39:01 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Chile: Earthquake  DHA-02


                    CHILE - EARTHQUAKE IN NORTHERN REGION
                                31 JULY 1995
                          INFORMATION REPORT NO. 2


  1.    ACCORDING  TO  PRELIMINARY  ESTIMATES CONVEYED BY DHA/UNDP RESIDENT
REPRESENTATIVE  SANTIAGO, EARTHQUAKE OF 30 JULY AFFECTED AN AREA FROM ARICA
TO LOS VILOS AS FOLLOWS:


  TOWN/CITY                   DEGREE ON MERCALLI SCALE

  ARICA                       4
  IQUIQUE                     6 - 7
  TOCOPILLA                   6 - 7
  CALAMA                      6 - 7
  CHUQUICAMATA                6
  ANTOFAGASTA                 6 - 7
  TALTAL                      6 - 7
  DIEGO DE ALMAGRO            6 - 7
  CHANARAL                    4 - 5
  CALDERA                     3 - 4
  COPIAPO                     5 - 6
  VALLENAR                    4 - 5
  LA SERENA                   4

  2.      THE  EARTHQUAKE  LASTED  ABOUT  2  MINUTES AND THERE WERE 6
  AFTERSHOCKS  BETWEEN  1.45AM  AND  7.00AM.  UPTO MORNING OF 31 JULY
  THERE  WERE  3  DEATHS AND 50 INJURED IN ADDITION TO 100 AFFECTED .
  ELECTRICITY,  WATER  SUPPLY  AND TELEPHONE WERE TEMPORARILY CUT BUT
  HAVE NOW BEEN RESTORED UP TO 70 %, EXCEPT WATER IN ANTOFAGASTA.

  3.      THE  WORST  DAMAGE  HAS  BEEN  IN  ANTOFAGASTA  PORT  WHICH
  MOBILIZES  COPPER  FROM NORTHERN MINES (THE MAIN NATIONAL RESOURCE)
  AND   IS   VITAL   FOR  BOLIVIAN  FOREIGN  TRADE.   80  %  OF  PORT
  INFRASTRUCTURE  WAS  DAMAGED.   WATER  TANK  ON ROOF OF ANTOFAGASTA
  REGIONAL HOSPITAL WAS BROKEN FLOODING THE 7 FLOORS OF THE BUILDING.

  4.      ONEMI  (OFFICE FOR EMERGENCIES WITHIN MINISTRY OF INTERIOR)
  INDICATED  THAT  55  LIGHTLY  BUILT  HOUSES WERE DAMAGED BUT RECENT
  PRIVATE AND PUBLIC BUILDINGS HAVE NOT BEEN DAMAGED.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22- 917 12 34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: TEL NO. +41-22- 917 20 10

  DESK OFFICER: MR. FABRIZIO GENTILONI , DIRECT TEL: +41-22- 917 3512
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22-917-
  28. 56
   TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22- 917. 00. 23
  INTERNET EMAIL: DHAGVA AT UN. ORG

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



