<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Thu, 3 Aug 95 12:27:06 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Disaster Information Administrator)
To: event@vita.org
Subject: Chile: Earthquake  DHA-03


                    CHILE - EARTHQUAKE IN NORTHERN REGION
                               3 AUGUST  1995
                          INFORMATION REPORT NO. 3


  1.    AS  A RESULT OF ENFORCEMENT OF ANTI-QUAKE BUILDING CODES CASUALTIES
OF  EARTHQUAKE  OF  7.8 MAGNITUDE IN RICHTER SCALE REMAIN LOW: 3 DEATHS, 58
INJURED.   ONLY  OLD  AND  LOW-INCOME  SELF-BUILT  DWELLINGS  WERE DAMAGED,
AFFECTING  SOME  1,200 PEOPLE.  ELECTRICITY AND WATER SUPPLY RESTORED FULLY
(30 PERCENT OF WATER BEING DISTRIBUTED BY TRUCK IN ANTOFAGASTA).

  2.     AREA IN WHICH EARTHQUAKE WAS FELT COVERS REGIONS I TO IV FOR
  A TOTAL OF MORE THAN 300,000 SQUARE KM AND 1.5 MILLION INHABITANTS.

  3.     TECHNICAL EVALUATION OF DAMAGE TO ANTOFAGASTA PORT UNDERWAY.
  IT IS ASSUMED THAT CAPACITY LEVEL ALMOST EQUIVALENT TO THAT OF LAST
  FEW  MONTHS  CAN  BE  REACHED BY NEXT WEEK.  THEREFORE, IT DOES NOT
  SEEM  NECESSARY  AT  THIS  STAGE  TO DIVERT COPPER EXPORTS TO OTHER
  PORTS.    REQUIREMENTS  FOR  PORT  REHABILITATION  ARE  TENTATIVELY
  ESTIMATED AT USDLRS 2 TO FIVE MILLION.

  4.       CHILEAN   GOVT   ALLOCATED   USDLRS   1.66   MILLION   FOR
  RECONSTRUCTION.

  5.       JAPANESE   CO-OPERATION   ENGINEERING   TEAM  ASSISTED  IN
  ASSESSMENT OF STRUCTURAL DAMAGE TO HOUSING AND PUBLIC BUILDINGS.

  6.      SITUATION  IN REGIONS II (MOST AFFECTED) AND III, ACCORDING
  TO DETAILED  REPORT  AVAILABLE  WITH DHA GENEVA:
  II REGION
  ANTOFAGASTA:  115 HOUSES DESTROYED, 630 PEOPLE HOMELESS, 45 OF WHOM
  SHELTERED  IN  SCHOOLS.   SOME ROADS HIT BY LANDSLIDES AND FISSURES
  BUT  STILL  TRANSITABLE.   CLASSES  RESUMED, EXCEPT IN FIVE DAMAGED
  SCHOOLS.
  SEVERAL  HOUSES  DAMAGED  IN  SETTLEMENTS OF MEJILLONES (100 PEOPLE
  AFFECTED),  TALTAL, CALAMA, SAN PEDRO DE ATACAMA AND TOCOPILLA (TWO
  SCHOOLS).
  250  EMERGENCY  SHELTERS  BEING  DISPATCHED  FROM SANTIAGO BY ONEMI
  (NATIONAL EMERGENCY OFFICE).
  III REGION (ATACAMA)
  MINES  AND  FIRMS  WORKING  NORMALLY, EXCEPT HYDROELECTRIC PLANT AT
  DIVISION SALVADOR. MINOR  DAMAGES BEING EVALUATED AND REPAIRED.


  TELEPHONE NO.  +41-22- 917 12 34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: TEL NO. +41-22- 917 20 10

  DESK OFFICER: MR. FABRIZIO GENTILONI , DIRECT TEL: +41-22- 917 3512
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MRS. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL:+41-22-917-
  28. 56

  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  FAX: +41-22- 917. 00. 23
  INTERNET EMAIL: DHAGVA AT UN. ORG

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



