<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Fri, 1 Sep 95 09:40:45 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Korea (ROK): Floods  DHA-04



              DEMOCRATIC PEOPLE'S REPUBLIC OF KOREA
                             FLOODS
                DHA GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 4
                        1 SEPTEMBER 1995

SITUATION
---------

1. UNDAC/WHO TEAM MADE ITS FIRST FIELD TRIP TO HWANGHAE PROVINCE,
SOUTH  OF  PYONGYANG, ON 31 SEPTEMBER.  TEAM VISITED AREAS AROUND
TOWNS OF SARIWON, UNPHA, AND RINSAN (IN CONNECTION WITH DAM BURST
AT SANGWOL RESERVOIR WEST OF RINSAN).

2. ACCORDING TO UNCONFIRMED DATA  PROVIDED  BY  PROVINCIAL  GOVT,
150,000  PEOPLE  WERE MADE HOMELESS IN HWANGHAE.  50,000 HA CROPS
(300,000  TONS,  OR  ABOUT  6  MONTHS  OF  FOOD  FOR   PROVINCE'S
POPULATION)  DAMAGED.   12  SCHOOLS, 14 HOSPITALS, AND 50 CLINICS
DESTROYED OR DAMAGED.  8  OUT  OF  PROVINCE'S  16  COUNTIES  HAVE
DAMAGED WATER SUPPLIES.  42 OUT OF 136 RESERVOIRS WERE DESTROYED,
OF WHICH SANGWOL RESERVOIR WAS THE LARGEST WITH ABOUT 11  MILLION
CUBIC METERS OF WATER.

NATIONAL RESPONSE
-------- --------

3. NON-STANDING COMMITTEES, RESPONSIBLE FOR WARNING  AS  WELL  AS
RESPONSE TO EMERGENCIES, HAVE BEEN WORKING ON ALL LEVELS.

ASSISTANCE NEEDS
---------- -----

4. AT THIS STAGE, MOST NEEDED ITEMS, AS REPORTED BY GOVT, ARE (IN
ORDER OF PRIORITY):
     - FOOD (PREDOMINANTLY RICE).
     - CLOTHING (APPROPRIATE TYPES AVAILABLE IN CHINA).
     - MEDICINES (WHO NEW EMERGENCY KITS. FURTHER DETAILS TO BE
       PROVIDED BY MINISTRY OF HEALTH).

5. GOVT ALSO INDICATED NEED FOR FOLLOWING ITEMS:
     - BLEACHING POWDER AND LIQUID CHLORINE FOR PURIFYING WATER.
     - WARM BLANKETS FOR COLD SEASON STARTING LATE SEPTEMBER.
     - FAMILY KITS.
     - EDUCATIONAL MATERIAL TO REPLACE THAT LOST IN FLOODS.
     - OIL AND FUEL TO OPERATE HEAVY EQUIPMENT IN RECONSTRUCTION
       WORK AHEAD.

6. UNDAC/WHO  TEAM  RECOMMENDS  THAT  RELIEF  ITEMS  BE  PROCURED
OUTSIDE THE COUNTRY, AS MOST OF THEM ARE NOT AVAILABLE LOCALLY.

7. DHA IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS A CHANNEL FOR  CASH  CONTRIBUTIONS
TO  BE  USED  DURING  IMMEDIATE RELIEF PHASE.  FUNDS ARE SPENT IN
COORDINATION WITH RELEVANT ORGANIZATION OF THE  UN  SYSTEM.   DHA
PROVIDES  DONOR GOVTS WITH WRITTEN CONFIRMATION OF UTILIZATION OF
FUNDS CONTRIBUTED.

8. TRANSFERS OF FUNDS  SHOULD  BE  MADE  TO  DHA  ACCOUNT  NUMBER
CO-590.160.1  AT  SWISS  BANK  CORPORATION,  CASE  POSTALE  2770,
CH-1211 GENEVA  2,  WITH FOLLOWING REFERENCE: NORTH KOREA-FLOODS,
DHA-GENEVA.

9. FOR COORDINATION PURPOSES,  DONORS  ARE  REQUESTED  TO  INFORM
DHA-GENEVA,    AS    INDICATED   BELOW,   OF   BILATERAL   RELIEF
MISSION/PLEDGES/CONTRIBUTIONS AND THEIR  CORRESPONDING  VALUE  BY
ITEM.


         + DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS - GENEVA +

TELEPHONE NO.+41-22/917.12.34
IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TEL NO. +41-22/917.20.10

