<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Wed, 6 Sep 95 12:58:45 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Korea (PRK): Floods  DHA-06


              DEMOCRATIC PEOPLE'S REPUBLIC OF KOREA
                             FLOODS
                DHA GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 6
                        6 SEPTEMBER 1995


1.  UN  RESIDENT  COORDINATOR  IN  PYONGYANG  IS   DIRECTING   UN
ASSESSMENT  MISSION WHICH HAS BEEN CARRIED OUT BY DHA-UNDAC TEAM,
FAO, UNICEF, WFP, AND WHO.

2. ON 12 SEPTEMBER, DHA GENEVA IS  TO  HOLD  INFORMATION  MEETING
WITH   GOVTS,   INTERGOVERNMENTAL  ORGANIZATIONS,  NGOS,  AND  UN
AGENCIES.  PRELIMINARY FINDINGS OF UN TEAM'S ASSESSMENT ARE TO BE
PRESENTED.

ASSISTANCE NEEDS
----------------

3. HIGHEST  PRIORITY  IS  TO  ASSIST  POPULATION  SUFFERING  FROM
IMMEDIATE  EFFECTS  OF  FLOODS.   TARGET POPULATION FOR EMERGENCY
ASSISTANCE THEREFORE IS 100,000 FAMILIES (500,000  PERSONS)  MADE
HOMELESS BY FLOODS.

4.   FOLLOWING RELIEF ITEMS ARE URGENTLY REQUIRED:

     -    WARM CLOTHING
     -    BLANKETS AND QUILTS
     -    FABRIC FOR CLOTHING
     -    KITCHEN UTENSILS
     -    MEDICINES
     -    FOOD (PREDOMINANTLY RICE).

5. DHA, IN CLOSE COOPERATION WITH  UN  RESIDENT  COORDINATORS  IN
PYONGYANG AND BEIJING, IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS A CHANNEL FOR CASH
CONTRIBUTIONS TO BE USED DURING IMMEDIATE RELIEF  PHASE  TO  MEET
REQUIREMENTS  IN  PARA  3 AND 4 ABOVE (WITH EXCEPTION OF FOOD AND
MEDICINES).  UN RESIDENT  COORDINATOR  IN  PYONGYANG  IS  ALREADY
PROCURING  CLOTHING,  BLANKETS,  AND  FAMILY  KITS  IN  CHINA, IN
COOPERATION WITH UNDP BEIJING.

6.  IT  SHOULD  BE  NOTED  THAT   FLOODS   DAMAGED   AGRICULTURAL
PRODUCTION, ALREADY HURT BY LAST YEAR'S HAIL STORM.  LOSS OF PART
OF THIS YEAR'S HARVEST, TOGETHER WITH POSSIBLE REDUCTION OF  NEXT
YEAR'S   EXPECTED   HARVEST   DUE   TO   DAMAGE  TO  AGRICULTURAL
INFRASTRUCTURE, WILL MAKE AGRICULTURAL  PRODUCTION  AND  FOOD  AN
INTERMEDIATE TO LONG-TERM PROBLEM.

7. FURTHERMORE, FLOODS CAUSED SERIOUS DAMAGE TO  ECONOMY  THROUGH
DESTRUCTION    OF    INDUSTRIAL    PRODUCTION    FACILITIES   AND
INFRASTRUCTURE.  THIS MAKES UP MOST  OF  USD  15  BILLION  DAMAGE
ESTIMATED BY GOVT.

CONTRIBUTIONS
-------------

8. FOLLOWING CONTRIBUTION HAS BEEN REPORTED SINCE SITREP NO 5:
UNICEF -- USD 50,000 (SOYBEANS).

9. TRANSFERS OF FUNDS TO DHA SHOULD BE MADE TO DHA ACCOUNT NUMBER
CO-590.160.1  AT  SWISS  BANK  CORPORATION,  CASE  POSTALE  2770,
CH-1211 GENEVA 2, WITH FOLLOWING REFERENCE:  DPR KOREA -  FLOODS,
DHA-GENEVA.

10.  FOR COORDINATION PURPOSES, DONORS ARE  REQUESTED  TO  INFORM
DHA-GENEVA,   AS   INDICATED   BELOW,   OF    BILATERAL    RELIEF
MISSION/PLEDGES/  CONTRIBUTIONS  AND THEIR CORRESPONDING VALUE BY
ITEM.

             + DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS - GENEVA +

TELEPHONE NO.   +41-22/917.12.34
IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY:  TEL NO. +41-22/917.20.10

DESK OFFICERS:  MS. K. GOTOH, DIRECT TEL. +41-22/917.12.58
