<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Wed, 13 Sep 1995 11:27:50 -0400 (EDT)
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Korea: Floods  DHA-07


              DEMOCRATIC PEOPLE'S REPUBLIC OF KOREA
                             FLOODS
                DHA GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 7
                        13 SEPTEMBER 1995


1.   ON 12 SEPTEMBER, DHA HELD INFORMATION MEETING IN GENEVA TO
PRESENT PRELIMINARY FINDINGS OF UN MISSION TO FLOOD AFFECTED
AREAS IN DPR KOREA.  MEETING WAS ATTENDED BY APPROXIMATELY 65
REPRESENTATIVES FROM GOVTS, INTER/NON-GOVERNMENTAL ORGANIZATIONS,
AND UN AGENCIES.

2.   FOLLOWING PRESENTATION ON OVERVIEW OF SITUATION BY DHA-
UNDAC TEAM, REPRESENTATIVES FROM UNICEF, WFP, FAO, AND WHO
DISCUSSED INITIAL ASSESSMENT IN THEIR RESPECTIVE FIELDS.

3.   REPORT ON PRELIMINARY FINDINGS OF UN MISSION IS AVAILABLE
FROM DHA.

APPEAL FOR ASSISTANCE
---------------------

4.   HIGHEST PRIORITY IS TO ASSIST 100,000 FAMILIES (500,000
PERSONS) CRITICALLY AFFECTED BY FLOODS.  THEY HAVE BEEN MADE
HOMELESS AND ARE CURRENTLY BEING SHELTERED IN PUBLIC BUILDINGS,
MAKESHIFT SHELTERS, OR HOMES OF RELATIVES AND OTHER FAMILIES.

5.   MOST URGENT NEEDS ARE FOR FOOD, SHELTER (INCLUDING BLANKETS
AND CLOTHING), AND HEALTH (MEDICINES).

6.   FOR INITIAL RESPONSE, DHA, TOGETHER WITH UN AGENCIES
CONCERNED, IS APPEALING FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE TO ADDRESS
IMMEDIATE RELIEF REQUIREMENTS AS FOLLOWS:

6.1  DHA/UNDP:  TOTAL USD 2,000,000

     PROVISION OF BLANKETS AND FAMILY         USD 2,000,000
     KITS TO INITIAL TARGET POPULATION
     OF 20,000 FAMILIES (100,000 PERSONS)

6.2  UNICEF:  TOTAL USD 4,462,000

     PHASE I: IMMEDIATE (THREE MONTHS) RELIEF REQUIREMENTS (USD
520,000, INCLUDING FREIGHT AND OTHER EXPENSES):

IN ADDITION TO USD 50,000 COMMITTED, UNICEF ISRE-PROGRAMMING
PART OF ITS ALREADY APPROVED COUNTRY PROGRAM FOR EMERGENCY
ACTIVITIES AND IS RELEASING FUNDS FROM EMERGENCY BOTH
OF WHICH WILL NEED TO BE REPLENISHED BY DONOR CONTRIBUTIONS.

     (1)  ORAL REHYDRATION: PROVISION OF          USD 20,000
     STRATEGIC RESERVE (250,000 LITRES)
     AT PROVINCE LEVEL

     (2)  SUPPLEMENTARY FEEDING: FOR 55,000       USD 335,250
     UNDER-FIVE CHILDREN IN DISPLACED
     FAMILIES FOR THREE MONTHS (745 TONS)

     (3)  MEASLES IMMUNIZATION:  FOR ALL
     UNDER-FIVE CHILDREN IN N. PYONGAN
     AND N. HWANGHAE PROVINCES

          650,000 DOSES OF VACCINE                USD 97,500
          650,000 DISPOSABLE SYRINGES             USD 65,000
          650,000 VITAMIN A CAPSULES               USD 1,300

     PHASE II:  LONGER-TERM REQUIREMENTS:

IMPLEMENTATION OF THIS PHASE WILL DEPEND ON REPLENISHMENT OF
RESOURCES DIVERTED IN PHASE I AS WELL AS ADDITIONAL FUNDS FOR
THESE ACTIVITIES.

     (1)  ORAL REHYDRATION:  REQUIRED             -
     ACCORDING TO SITUATION

     (2)  MEASLES IMMUNIZATION:  FOR ALL
     UNDER-FIVE CHILDREN EXCEPT FOR N.
     PYONGAN AND N. HWANGHAE PROVINCES

          2,600,000 DOSES OF VACCINE              USD 390,000
          2,600,000 DISPOSABLE SYRINGES           USD 260,000
          2,600,000 VITAMIN A CAPSULES            USD  52,000

     (3)  SUPPLEMENTARY FEEDING:  FOR           USD 3,240,000
     HALF OF UNDER-FIVE CHILDREN IN
     AFFECTED AREAS FOR SIX MONTHS (7,200 TONS)

6.3  WHO:  TOTAL USD 2,000,000

     (1)  ESSENTIAL MEDICINES: 150 HEALTH       USD 1,500,000
     KITS

     (2)  BASIC MEDICAL EQUIPMENT: FOR 300      USD    45,000
     DAMAGED PRIMARY HEALTH CARE CLINICS

     (3)  LABORATORY SUPPORT:  REAGENTS         USD    80,000
     AND EQUIPMENT FOR 145 COUNTRY LABS,
     AND WHO EXPERT FOR ONE WEEK

     (4)  WATER AND SANITATION:  CHLORINE         USD 150,000
     POWDER AND TWO WHO EXPERTS IN CDD
     AND WATER SUPPLY FOR ONE WEEK

     (5)  SURVEILLANCE SYSTEMS AND                USD  75,000
     REPORTING (NUTRITION, WATER QUALITY,
     VECTOR CONTROL, AND MORBIDITY):
     TRAINING AND WHO STAFF FOR ONE WEEK

     (6)  BASIC ADMINISTRATIVE AND                 USD  50,000
     TECHNICAL SUPPORT TO MINISTRY OF
     PUBLIC HEALTH

     (7)  TRADITIONAL MEDICINES:                    USD 70,000
     BASIC INGREDIENTS

(8)  FREIGHT COSTS                                 USD 30,000

6.4  WFP: TOTAL USD 7,250,250

     (1)  PROVISION OF RICE FOR 500,000          SD 6,480,000
     PERSONS FOR 90 DAYS (20,250 TONS)

     (2)  PROVISION OF VEGETABLE OIL FOR          USD 695,250
     500,000 PERSONS FOR 90 DAYS (675 TONS)

     (3)  MONITORING                               USD 75,000

7.   ADDITIONALLY, SERIOUS SHORTAGE OF FUEL IS REPORTED, WHICH
MIGHT HAMPER DISTRIBUTION OF RELIEF ITEMS WITHIN COUNTRY, AS
WELL AS SLOW DOWN RESTORATION OF CRITICAL FACILITIES AND
INFRASTRUCTURE.  THEREFORE, PROVISION OF FUEL MAY BECOME
IMPORTANT COMPONENT FOR EMERGENCY RESPONSE.

8.   FLOODS ALSO CAUSED SEVERE DAMAGE TO AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTION
AS WELL AS LONG-TERM EFFECT ON ECONOMY THROUGH DESTRUCTION OF
PRODUCTION FACILITIES AND INFRASTRUCTURE.  THESE INTERMEDIATE TO
LONG-TERM ISSUES WILL BE ASSESSED MORE THOROUGHLY AND MAY BE
INCLUDED IN LATER APPEALS FOR ASSISTANCE.
9.   FAO IS FIELDING A MISSION TO DPR KOREA TO CARRY OUT
COMPREHENSIVE ASSESSMENT OF EMERGENCY NEEDS IN AGRICULTURAL
SECTOR, WHICH WILL BE PRESENTED TO INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY.
UNESCO IS ALSO FIELDING A MISSION TO ASSESS DAMAGE TO SCHOOLS.

RELIEF COORDINATION
-------------------

10.  DHA IS PLANNING, IN CONSULTATION WITH UN RESIDENT
COORDINATOR IN PYONGYANG, TO STRENGTHEN RELIEF COORDINATION AND
MONITORING CAPACITIES IN THE FIELD BY DISPATCHING EXPERTS IN
RELIEF MANAGEMENT AND  LOGISTICS, WHICH WILL BE FINANCED BY SWISS
GOVTERNMENT.

11.  DHA, IN CLOSE COOPERATION WITH UN RESIDENT COORDINATORS IN
PYONGYANG AND BEIJING, IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS A CHANNEL FOR CASH
CONTRIBUTIONS TO BE USED DURING IMMEDIATE RELIEF PHASE TO MEET
ABOVE DEFINED REQUIREMENTS.  TASK FORCES HAVE BEEN ESTABLISHED IN
UNDP PYONGYANG AND BEIJING TO MANAGE PROCUREMENT OF RELIEF ITEMS
IN CHINA.

CONSOLIDATED LIST OF CONTRIBUTIONS
----------------------------------

12.  FOLLOWING CONTRIBUTIONS HAVE BEEN REPORTED TO DHA SO FAR.

     UN ORGANIZATIONS:

     DHA                 USD 50,000 EMERGENCY GRANT

     UNICEF              USD 50,000

     WFP                 USD 50,000

     UNDP                USD 50,000 (CLOTHING, BLANKETS, AND
                         FAMILY KITS BEING PROCURED IN CHINA)

     WHO                 USD 100,000 (ESSENTIAL MEDICINES AND
                         CHLORINE POWDER)

     UNESCO              USD 40,000

     GOVERNMENTS:

     NORWAY              USD 100,000 (THROUGH DHA)

