<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 5 Sep 95 15:34:39 EDT
From: Emergency Information Administrator <incident@lan.vita.org>
Subject: Caribbean: Hurricane Luis  DHA-01




                          CARIBBEAN - HURRICANE LUIS
                      DHA-GENEVA INFORMATION REPORT NO 1


  THIS  MESSAGE  IS  NOT  AN  OFFICIAL  HURRICANE  WARNING OR ALERT FOR ANY
COUNTRY.

  1.      THE  US  NATIONAL  WEATHER SERVICE FORECASTS THAT HURRICANE
  LUIS WILL REACH THE LEEWARD ISLANDS TODAY. AS OF 0900 UTC HURRICANE
  WARNINGS  REMAIN  IN  EFFECT  FOR  THE  ISLANDS  OF  THE  NORTHEAST
  CARIBBEAN  FROM DOMINICA NORTHWARD TO PUERTO RICO. A TROPICAL STORM
  WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FOR MARTINIQUE AND ST LUCIA.

  2.      THE  US  NATIONAL  WEATHER SERVICE NOTES THAT THE CENTRE OF
  HURRICANE LUIS WAS 17.4 NORTH, 61.4 WEST AS OF 0900 UTC, ABOUT 55KM
  NORTHEAST  OF  ANTIGUA  AND  BARBUDA AND 105KM NORTH OF GUADELOUPE.
  LUIS  HAS  SLOWED  DOWN  AND  IS  MOVING  WESTWARDS AT 15KM/HR WITH
  MAXIMUM  SUSTAINED  WINDS  OF  220  KM/HR.  A  GRADUAL  TURN TO THE
  WEST-NORTHWEST  IS  EXPECTED  LATER  TODAY. LUIS REMAINS A CATEGORY
  FOUR HURRICANE ON THE SAFFIR/SIMPSON SCALE.

  3.     THE CARIBBEAN DISASTER EMERGENCY RESPONSE AGENCY (CDERA) HAS
  ISSUED  A  REPORT  OUTLINING THE STATE OF PREPAREDNESS AMONG ISLAND
  COMMUNITIES.  THE REGIONAL RESPONSE MECHANISM HAS BEEN PUT ON ALERT
  AND  CONTACTS  ESTABLISHED  WITH ALL NATIONAL DISASTER COORDINATORS
  (NDCS)  IN  THE  IMMEDIATELY THREATENED AREAS. EMERGENCY OPERATIONS
  CENTRES (EOCS) HAVE BEEN ACTIVATED.

  4.      INITIAL  PREPAREDNESS  ACTIVITIES  HAVE  BEEN  PUT IN PLACE
  INCLUDING   CLOSURE   OF   SCHOOLS,   CHECKING   OF   SHELTERS  AND
  PREPOSITIONING  OF  SUPPLIES. PROVISIONS ARE BEING MADE TO ORGANIZE
  DAMAGE ASSESSMENT MISSIONS IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE ALL-CLEAR HAS BEEN
  ANNOUNCED.  ANTICIPATED  RELIEF NEEDS HAVE BEEN IDENTIFIED FOR EACH
  ISLAND.  COMMAND  AND  CONTROL  OF  THE LUIS OPERATION WILL BE FROM
  BARBADOS.

  5.      THE  CDERA  COORDINATING UNIT IS COLLABORATING CLOSELY WITH
  OTHER  REGIONAL  AND  INTERNATIONAL AGENCIES TO ENSURE A TIMELY AND
  APPROPRIATE  RESPONSE  IS  AVAILABLE  IN THE EVENT THAT THE CURRENT
  LEVEL OF THREAT IS MAINTAINED.


  TELEPHONE NO:+41/22/9171234
