<title></title><BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/bground.jpg"><PRE>
Date: Tue, 12 Sep 95 12:38:07 EDT
From: incident@vita.org (Emergency Information Administrator)
Subject: Caribbean: Hurricane  DHA-05


                    CARIBBEAN-HURRICANE LUIS
                       ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA
                   DHA SITUATION REPORT NO. 5
                        12 SEPTEMBER 1995

1. PAHO ASSESSMENT MISSION IDENTIFIED THE  FOLLOWING  NEEDS  WITH
REGARD  TO  WATER  DISTRIBUTION,  BASIC  SANITATION,  CLEANING OF
DEBRIS, VECTOR CONTROL, HOSPITALS/HEALTH CENTRES AND SHELTERS.

2. WATER SUPPLY SYSTEM IN CAPITAL ST JOHN'S IN FULL OPERATION
SINCE 8 SEPTEMBER.  80 PER CENT OF ISLAND-WIDE CAPACITY RESTORED
ON 11 SEPTEMBER.  IN BARBUDA NO IMPACT ON WATER SUPPLY.  WATER
HOWEVER VERY BRACKISH.  WATER FOR DRINKING AND FOOD PREPARATION
TAKEN FROM RAINWATER CISTERNS.

NEEDS FOR  ANTIGUA:   400  SQFT  PLASTIC  SHEETING  FOR  PUMPING
STATION  AND  400  SQFT  PLASTIC  SHEETING  FOR ROOF OF TREATMENT
PLANT, 100 DRUMS AT 50LBS OF HYPOCHLORITE GRANULAR 70 PER CENT AI,
ONE  25KVA  MOBILE  STANDBY  GENERATOR  FOR SURFACE WATER PUMPING
STATION.

NEEDS FOR BARBUDA: COOKING GAS FOR BOILING OF DRINKING WATER.

3. FLOOD WATER WITH HIGH LEVEL OF FAECAL MATTER IN LOW-LYING  AND
LOW-INCOME    AREAS.     PIT    LATRINES   FLOODED.    CASES   OF
GASTRO-ENTIRITIS AND  WORM  INFESTATION  LIKELY  TO  BECOME  MORE
FREQUENT.

NEEDS FOR ANTIGUA: 10,000 SACHETS OF ORS

NEEDS FOR BARBUDA: 1,000 SACHETS OF ORS.

4. CLEANING OF DEBRIS HAS BEGUN WITH GOOD  COOPERATION  FROM  THE
PUBLIC  IN  ANTIGUA.   IN  BARBUDA, PROPER CLEAN UP HAS YET TO BE
STARTED.

NEED FOR ANTIGUA:  20 CHAIN SAWS, 200 GLOVES, 100 SHOVELS, 100
FORKS.

5. MOSQUITO POPULATION IS INCEASING.  LARGE  NUMBER  OF  STAGNANT
POOLS RODENTS DEPRIVED OF THEIR NESTS ARE A PROBLEM.

NEEDS FOR ANTIGUA:  2 DRUMS OF MALATHION 10 PER CENT,  10  FOGGING
MACHINES, 30 DRUMS OF RAT POISON.

NEEDS FOR BARBUDA:  1 DRUM OF MALATHION 10  PER  CENT,  2  FOGGING
MACHINES, 2 DRUMS OF RAT POISON.

6. DAMAGE CAUSED TO ROOFING  OF  HEALTH  CENTRES  AND  HOSPITALS,
WARDS  AND  STOREROOM  FLOODED,  RUNNING WATER CUT OFF OR REDUCED
SUPPLY, FLUSH TOILETS OUT OF  USE,  DAMAGE  TO  WATER  PUMPS  AND
PLUMBING.

NEEDS FOR ANTIGUA:  ROOFING MATERIAL, FOOD SUPPLIES FOR  PATIENTS
(80  PATIENTS  IN  MENTAL  HOSPITAL  AND 77 PATIENTS IN GERIATRIC
HOSPITAL) , DETERGENT, SOAP, DIESEL  OPERATED  WATER  PUMP  (SELF
SUCTION) FOR MENTAL HOSPITAL, BED LINEN FOR 157 PATIENTS.

NEEDS FOR BARBUDA:  ROOFING MATERIAL, ANTIBIOTICS, AND ANTIBIOTIC
OINTMENTS, T. TOXOIDE, DRESSING GAUZE, DISINFECTANTS.

7. NO NEED FOR FIELD HOSPITALS

8. SOME 1,600 PERSONS STILL IN SHELTERS.   NO  WATER  SUPPLY.
FLUSH  TOILETS  BLOCKED.   SHELTER  SIZE  VARIES FROM FOUR TO 200
PERSONS.  SHELTER MANAGEMENT IS TRYING TO GROUP PEOPLE IN  LARGER
SHELTERS.

NEEDS:   COLLAPSIBLE  WATER  CONTAINERS,  TOILET   PAPER,   SOAP,
DETERGENTS, BUCKETS, COOKING GAS.

9. DONORS WISHING TO CONTRIBUTE TOWARDS REQUIREMENTS OF MEDICINES
AND MEDICAL SUPPLIES, SANITATION AND VECTOR CONTROL ARE REQUESTED
TO CONSULT WITH:

PAHO/WASHINGTON:  EMERGENCY PREPAREDNESS AND DISASTER RELIEF  ===
COORDINATION PROGRAM (PED)

TELEPHONE NO. +1/202 861-4325
FAX NO. +1/202 775-4578

10. DHA IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS A CHANNEL FOR CASH  CONTRIBUTIONS
TO  BE  USED  DURING  IMMEDIATE RELIEF PHASE.  FUNDS ARE SPENT IN
COORDINATION WITH RELEVANT ORGANIZATIONS OF THE  UN  SYSTEM,  DHA
PROVIDES   DONOR   GOVERNMENTS   WITH   WRITTEN  CONFIRMATION  OF
UTILIZATION OF FUNDS CONTRIBUTED.

11. TRANSFERS OF FUNDS  SHOULD  BE  MADE TO  DHA  ACCOUNT  NUMBER
CO-590.160.1  AT  SWISS  BANK  CORPORATION,  CASE  POSTALE  2770,
CH-1211  GENEVA  2,  WITH  FOLLOWING  REFERENCE:    ANTIGUA   -
HURRICANE LUIS, DHA-GENEVA.

12.  FOR COORDINATION PURPOSES, DONORS ARE  REQUESTED  TO  INFORM
DHA-GENEVA,  AS  INDICATED  BELOW,  OF BILATERAL RELIEF MISSIONS,
PLEDGES, CONTRIBUTIONS AND THEIR CORRESPONDING VALUE BY ITEM.


         = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS - GENEVA +


TELEPHONE NO. +41 22-917-12.34
IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: TELEPHONE +41-22-917.20.10
                     ----

DESK OFFICER: MR. E. HAEGGLUND DIRECT TEL: +41-22-917.32.99
PRESS TO CONTACT: MS. M. MOULIN-ACEVEDO,
                  DIRECT TEL: +41-22-917.28.56

TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
