<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>TL PR News FAQ</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="/tlpr/tlprlogo.gif" WIDTH="225" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottomNATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><p><font size=+2>FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions)</font></center><p><b>Q. What is the purpose of Travel Leader PR News?</b><br><b>A.</b> A.To serve travel writers. They increasingly are using The Internet's World Wide Web as an information resource, many checking it daily.  <p><b>Q. Is Travel Leader PR News  redundant with press releases already distributed by other means?</b><br><b>A.</b> Not at all, because the main purpose of Travel Leader PR News  is to provide an archive of releases and background pieces readily available to writers at any time. Writers no longer will have to fish out news releases or press kits sent them weeks ago, or request new ones. Recent release hyperlinked headlines, however, receive immediate visibility on the "What's New?" page, remaining there for 30 days.<p><b>Q. Do members have their own proprietary sites within Travel Leader PR News?</b><br><b>A.</b> Yes. They even can have its own URLs to allow access directly from other sites, and have their  own "home pages" with their own color logos and directories of releases available online.<p><b>Q. How will travel editors and writers know that Travel Leader PR News  exists on the Internet, and where to find it?</b><br><b>A.</b> Initially the travel pressincluding both consumer and trade resources, as well as electronic and print mediawill receive a mailing that explains the service, that it is free to them, and that lists its members.<p>A ROLODEX card containing the Travel Leader PR News URL (http://www.travelleader.com) also will be included for continual reference.<p>In addition, a sweepstakes with highly attractive prizes will be offered exclusively for members of the travel press. Other relevant high traffic Internet sites also will be linked, as will the consumer and industry newsletters at the Travel Leader Services site.<p><b>Q. Is Travel Leader PR News  redundant with members' existing Web sites? And can links be established to jump to them?</b><br><b>A.</b> Travel Leader PR News  exists primarily to serve the press. Consumer traffic ("hits") nevertheless will occur as a bonus. Members having Web sites of their own, therefore, may want hyperlinks. Those carrying 10 or more pages monthly (three month minimum) on Travel Leader PR News  can be linked to their home pages at no charge.<p><b>Q. How affordable is the service?</b><br><b>A.</b> Very affordable indeed....Each ongoing page (up to 300 words) online costs just $7.00 per month after the first month. The rate for the first month is $25.00 per page, including the listing in "What's New?"<p>Package rates also are available for members wishing to archive the body of their press releases for reference by writers. (SeePress Kit Continuity Package Rates in the Fact Sheet.) <p>For more information call DANesbett:203-655-4947<br>fax: 203-662-0455<br>e-mail: <a href="mailto:dnesbett@travelleader.com">dnesbett@travelleader.com</a><p><center><a href="http://www.travelleader.com/butbar2.map"><IMG SRC="http://www.travelleader.com/tlsbutbr.gif" ISMAP border=0 WIDTH="390" HEIGHT="78" ALIGN=bottom></a></center></body></html>
