<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>About TLS Page</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="tlsslogo.gif" WIDTH="225" HEIGHT="55" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><p><font size=+2>Who is behind Travel Leader Services?</font></center><p>The principal is DANesbett who has written and edited travel-related publications, as well as supervised and consulted on travel marketing projects, for over 20 years. In 1973 he wrote the original U.S. marketing and advertising plan for Cancun, where the first hotel was just being completed.  The client was the Mexican government.<p>In 1982 he founded The Travel Market Leader to fill an industry need of readable, expert and research-based travel marketing information. Articles bring to focus a broad travel industry background, personal contacts, and other resources.<p>His articles also have appeared in consumer publications such as Ski and Skiing magazines, The Saturday Review and Business Traveler International, as well as most of the leading travel trade publications. In addition, he authored a series of consumer lifestyle newsletters for the Hearst Corporation, namely Woman Power Perspectives and The Affluent Consumer. <p>Nesbett edits the Travel Leader and Travel Market Leader newsletters, and manages their marketing, and that of Travel Leader PR News. He can be reached at 203 655 4947 or at PO Box 2397, Darien, CT 06820. Fax is 203 662 0455;  e-mail is <a href="mailto:dnesbett@travelleader.com">dnesbett@travelleader.com</a><p>Design and World Wide Web Site management is by Kenneth Shafton of Stamford, Connecticut. Shafton is a recognized pioneer is the field of computer-assisted design and an expert in online technology. E-Mail is <a href="mailto:webmaster@travelleader.com">webmaster@travelleader.com</a><p>Technical interface is handled by NetFocus,Inc. The server is maintained by Futuris, Inc..  Both also are located in Stamford, Connecticut. <p><a href="http://www.travelleader.com/butbar2.map"><IMG SRC="http://www.travelleader.com/tlsbutbr.gif" ISMAP border=0 WIDTH="390" HEIGHT="78" ALIGN=bottom></a></UL><P><CENTER></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
