<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>TL PR News Fact Sheet</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="/tlpr/tlprlogo.gif" WIDTH="225" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR><BR></CENTER><FONT size=+2>Fact Sheet</FONT><P><A HREF="#descrip">Description of the Service</A> <BR><BR><A HREF="#rates">Rates and Billing</A> <BR><BR><A HREF="#press">Press Kit Continuity Package Rates</A> <BR><BR><A HREF="#member">Membership and Placement Policies</A> <BR><BR><A HREF="#procedure">Procedures for Members Submitting Releases to PostOnline</A> <BR><BR><A HREF="#general">General</A> <BR><BR><BR><FONT size=+2><A NAME="descrip"></A>Description of the Service</FONT> <br>The service is designed to make its use by the travel press as easy as possible, whether they are browsing for ideas or researching a story on assignment. Writers and editors, including columnists and news directors at radio and TV stations, are informed and reminded of Travel Leader PR News' &quot;Web&quot; address (www.travelleader.com) via an initial Rolodex card mailing, quarterly newsletter mailings, and other activities thereafter. Registration for sweepstakes drawings and Travel Leader Services' own consumer and industry newsletters linked to the Travel Leader PR News (PRN) site will promote repeat visits. <p>Various routes of accessing documents on the service are available to the press. The name of each member (or client) is listed according to destination or service category, and is linked to the member's Travel Leader PR News &quot;contents page&quot;. The headline of the release or background paper appears on the &quot;What's New?&quot; page for 30 days, and on the member's own PRN &quot;contents page,&quot; in both cases being linked to the full text of the PR document. <br><br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><FONT size=+2><A NAME="rates"></A>Rates and Billing<br></FONT> 1. The rate is $25.00 per page or portion thereof, which covers its being electronically entered and maintained online for the first month. The rate is $7.00 per page for each month the document remains thereafter. All billing statements are based upon the documents that are online on the final business day of each month. Package rates also are available that represent substantial savings. (see Package Rates below) <p>2. A page is defined as up to 300 words. For example, a release of 500 words would be billed at $50 for the first month, and $14 for each month thereafter. <p>3. All releases requiring scanning from mailed or faxed hard copy incur an additional one-time fee of $5 per page. <p>4. Establishment of each member's "contents page" will incur a one-time fee of $50 for scanning and positioning the logo. For initial postings of 25 or more pages, this fee is waived. If contact names, address, phone and fax numbers do not appear in the text of each release, instructions should be given for this information to be incorporated in the "contents page" header design. A press release letterhead usually can serve as artwork for the "contents page" elements. <p>5. Billing statements will be sent only to.U.S.and Canadian billing addresses. Remittance must be in dollars drawn on U.S.or Canadian banks.(An addditional $2.50 clearance fee per check is charged for all checks drawn on Canadian banks.) All statements are due upon receipt, and will be in arrears at the end of the next calendar month. If the member is in arrears, all documents may be automatically removed from online. <br><br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><FONT size=+2><A NAME="press"></A>Press Kit Continuity Package Rates</FONT> <br># of Pages Online  Annual Rate <I>(billed quarterly) </I><br>10............................$1,250 <br>25 ...........................$1,950 <br>50 ...........................$3,450 <br>75 ...........................$5,150 <br>100 .........................$5,950 <br><p><I>Package Price Includes:</I> <UL><LI>Initial placement of all releases online from supplied disk or e-mail. <LI>Scanning of supplied art for color logo for contents page <LI>E-mail link <LI>Hyperlinks to members' Web sites (with reciprocal links). <LI>Entering new/replacement pages annually up to twice the number of pages online (i.e. a 50-page plan allows for 100 replacement pages annually). <LI>Extra pages billed at prorated package rate. <LI>Listed in mailings to over 1,000 travel press </UL><br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><FONT size=+2><A NAME="member"></A>Placement Policies</FONT> <br>1. Members simply fill out a registration form the first time they use Travel Leader PR News. This records contact names, billing and other addresses, telephone, fax and e-mail numbers, and provides that each member understands and accepts the procedures, terms, and conditions for using the service. Unless expressly agreed to in writing by Travel Leader, no terms or conditions, printed, written or oral, accompanying releases or otherwise expressed by the member that conflict with this Fact Sheet shall not be binding on Travel Leader. <p>2. Once the New Member Registration Form has been filed with Travel Leader Services, either as hard copy or electronically via the WWW site, releases transmitted to the service automatically are placed online. Members are responsible for notifying Travel Leader Services when the release is to be removed from the service. If this is known at the time of the posting, this may be specified then, and plainly marked to that effect..."remove after 30 days"<p>3. Releases will receive the fastest execution and incur the least possibility for electronic error if they are transmitted via e-mail. Floppy disks also may be sent, and in fact, are recommended if a number of releases are to be posted at a given time, such as in the initial establishment of a site on the service, when hard copy of the member's logo also should be included to be scanned as the heading for the "contents page"<br> <br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><FONT size=+2><A NAME="procedure"></A>Procedures for Members Submitting Releases to Post Online</FONT><br> <I>Members- Kindly submit releases, whether on disk or via e-mail, in the following format: </I><UL><LI>Single-spaced <LI>12 point New Or Times New Roman font<LI>Left-justified (i.e.no centering) <LI>No accents above or below letters, underlining, italicizing, etc. <LI>Text Only documents. simply select &quot;Save AS...&quot; under the File menu and choose &quot;Text only,&quot; Plain Text,&quot; or simply &quot;Text,&quot; to save documents in basic ASCII format. </UL><p>Addresses and phone numbers: <p>The e-mail address is: prnews@travelleader.com <p>Releases should be sent as attachments &quot;pasted&quot; to the transmitting document. <p>The postal address is: Webmaster Travel Leader PR News PO Box 2397 Darien, CT 06820 <p>The fax number is 203 662 0455 <p>The telephone number for all inquiries is 203 655 4947 <br><br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><FONT size=+2><A NAME="general"></A>General</FONT> Travel Leader Services, the service provider, has the right to refuse material deemed by them to be salacious or otherwise inappropriate, are not responsible for, and disclaim any liability for, the opinions or information expressed in the material provided by members, and disclaim any responsibility for errors in material provided by clients, in transcription, or other electronic errors. <p>In consideration of the publication of public relations and advertising materials, the originator and agency, jointly and severally, will unconditionally indemnify and save the publisher, its agents, employees and officers, harmless, on demand, from and against any and all loss, liability and expense (including reasonable attorneys fees) suffered or incurred by reason of any claims, proceedings or suits for libel, violation of right of privacy, plagiarism, copyright infringement, and any other claims or suits based on the contents or subject matter of such public relations and advertising materials. New York State law will govern the parties' agreement. <p><br><a href="#top"><img src="up.gif" border=0 alt="Up"></a><hr><p><A HREF="http://www.travelleader.com/butbar2.map"><IMG SRC="http://www.travelleader.com/tlsbutbr.gif"ISMAP BORDER="0" WIDTH="390" HEIGHT="78" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></UL></BODY></HTML>
