<br><b>Contact:</b>
<dl><dd>Liliane Menin-Opsomer
<dd>Press and Public Relations Manager
<dd>e-mail: <a href="mailto:belpress@nyfer.blythe.org"> belpress@nyfer.blythe.org</a>
</dl>

<p><center><b>"FROM ENSOR TO DELVAUX" MAJOR EXHIBIT TO BE HELD 
AT THE PROVINCIAL MUSEUM OF MODERN ART IN OSTEND 
FROM OCTOBER 5, 1996 UNTIL FEBRUARY 2, 1997</center></b>


<p>The best of twentieth-century painting is brought together in an exhibition at the Provincial Museum of Modern Art in Ostend.  "From Ensor to Delvaux" will present a unique selection of the best works by Ensor, Spilliaert, Permeke, Magritte and Delvaux.

<p>The collection surveys modern and contemporary visual art and includes: James Ensor (1860-1949) and Leon Spilliaert (1881-1946) both born in Ostend; and Constant Permeke (1885-1952) who worked and lived there for some time.  Together with the Brussels artists, Rene Magritte (1898-1967)  and Paul Delvaux (1897-1991) these artists form the core of modern art history in Belgium.

<p>Since art and tourism prove to be good partners, special packages are offered which include a guided tour of the exhibition and a night's stay with other possible tourist options.  In Ostend itself or the immediate surroundings there are several splendid museums which could form an interesting supplement to the exhibition: the Ensor house in Ostend, or the Paul Delvaux Museum in St. Idelsbald/Koksijde.  The Belgian art cities of Bruges, Ghent and Antwerp are less than one hour drive away.  

<p>The exhibition is open from Saturday 5 October 1996 until Sunday 2 February 1997.  Open every day from 10 AM until 6 PM.  Closed on Mondays.   Guided tours in english are available.  Entrance fee 385 BF (+/- $14).  For further information contact : The Provincial Museum of Modern Art, Romestraat, 11, 8400 Ostend or the Tourist Office of Ostend, Monacoplein,2 in 8400 Ostend.  (Tel: 011 32 59/70 11 99 - Fax: 011 32 59/70 34 77)

</body>
