<br><b>INTER-CONTINENTAL CONCIERGES THE WORLD OVER UNVEIL 
CONFIDENTIAL TRAVEL INFORMATION</b>


<p>
<center><b>Concierge Confidential: 50 Years of Closely Guarded Travel Tips and Other Priceless 
Information is Available Free</b></center>

<p><b>LONDON (May 10, 1996)</b> -- When in Rome?  Do what the Inter-Continental concierge suggests:  rent a bike at the Spanish steps and pedal through Borghese park.  And when in Paris, San Francisco, Rio, Bali or Nairobi, do what Inter-Continentals coterie of concierges recommend to turn an ordinary trip into an extraordinary experience.

<p>As a service to travelers, Inter-Continental has published closely guarded travel tips, trivia and other priceless information from around the world in a booklet, called Concierge Confidential, that is free for the asking.  Here is a sampling of  recommendations:

<ul>
<li>Turn a bad hair day into a great one at Berlins Friseur Museum where the featured attraction is the history of hair.

<li>Take to the lake.  While the plumes of water shot from Genevas trademark Jet d'Eau are visible for miles, the best place to watch is from the quai Gustave Ador. 

<li>Set your sights on a samovar, military regalia or Imperial jewels at the Izmailovo flea market in Moscow and go via Europes grandest subway system.

<li>Go really down under on the Egouts de Paris tour which traces the history of the Paris sewer system.

<li>Savor New York's most expensive and well-known restaurants at lunch when many offer an affordable prix-fixe menu.

<li>Have your concierge call ahead, for the only way to purchase fine Finnish fabrics at the Marimekko Factory is by appointment only.  
</ul>

<p>To receive a free copy of Concierge Confidential,  call toll-free at (800)-615-6085.  For reservations, contact your local travel agent or Inter-Continental reservations at 1-800-327-0200.

</body>
