<html><head><title>TIA</title></head><body bgcolor="ffffff"><font size=-1>DATE:<br>March 7, 1996<br>CONTACT:<br>Dexter Koehl<br>Shawn Flaherty<br>(202) 408-2137</font><p><center><font size=+2>1995: COST OF TRAVEL KEEPS PACE WITH INFLATION</font></center><p>WASHINGTON, DC--The Travel Industry Association of America's Travel Price Index (TPI) registered a 2.9 percent increase in 1995, virtually matching the increase in the Consumer Price Index--the index measuring the rate of inflation. <p>"Traveling still remains a great American affordable pastime," said TIA President William S. Norman.  "Costs have kept pace with the low rate of inflation, and were it not for higher increases in the cost of lodging (+4.1%)  and entertainment (+3.7%), the overall cost of the travel experience in the United States in 1994 would have been less than the rate of inflation."<p>Data for December 1995 reveal few surprises.  Airline fares dropped 6.8 percent from November; this reflects a number of fare sales that took place during the month.  Motor fuel  prices, which had dropped 6.1 percent in November 1995, dropped another 1.9 percent in December as world oil supplies, while not necessarily "glutting" the market, remain plentiful.<p>The Travel Price Index, a product of TIA's research department, is based on the Consumer Price Index and measures seasonally unadjusted changes in the cost of travel in the United States.  It reached 158.3 (1982-84 = 100) in December 1995.  The Travel Price Index indicates that change in prices of travel goods and services available to the consumer in the U.S. and does not necessarily represent changes in the average fares, rates, and other costs travelers actually paid.<p><p><hr>TIA is the national, non-profit organization representing all components of the $430 billion U.S. travel industry.  TIA's mission is to promote travel to and within the U.S.<p><center><a href="http://www.travelleader.com/butbar2.map"><IMG SRC="http://www.travelleader.com/tlsbutbr.gif" ISMAP border=0 WIDTH="390" HEIGHT="78" ALIGN=bottom></a></center></body></html>
